title: pecan oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oatmeal, flour, pecans, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, combine milk, eggs and butter.
Beat with fork until well combined.
Pour the egg mixture over the dry ingredients.
Stir just until they are combined.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Layer sliced Twinkies in pan.
Slice bananas on top of Twinkies.
Mix pudding with 2 cups of milk and spread on top of bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding mixture.
Top with whipped topping.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine milk, soup, cheese and chicken.
Spread half the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole dish.
Lay cooked broccoli crossways and top with remaining chicken mixture. Combine crumbs with butter and spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna garden salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna, blend with next 6 ingredients.
Chill until serving time.
Just before serving, stir in onion.
Arrange lettuce on serving platter.
Mound tuna mixture in center.
Garnish with green pepper and cucumber.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Combine chicken and cream cheese and season to taste.
Unroll dough into triangles.
Divide chicken among triangles and pinch edges to seal and enclose chicken.
(You will have some odd shaped bundles.)
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Make gravy and serve.

title: cheese tart
directions: Place pita bread, rounded side up, on a cookie sheet.
Mix tomato paste, garlic, oil and basil. Spread mixture thinly on bread.
Arrange, alternating slices of cheese and tomato on top. Sprinkle with pepper. Bake in a preheated 400° hot oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve garnished with sprig of fresh basil.

title: supreme green beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add mustard and cheese; mix lightly.
Place in 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Top with nuts.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until creamy and smooth.
Stir in butter. Remove from heat; stir in green pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix well and pour over cream cheese.
Stir until blended, then chill. Makes about 1 pint.

title: come spring salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and whip until blended well. Add macaroni and vegetables; toss lightly.
Chill and serve.
Makes a very large batch.

title: buttermilk cheese quiche
directions: Combine eggs and buttermilk; blend in other ingredients; pour into heated pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt.
Combine vinegar, water and egg.
Add to flour mixture; mix to form dough.
Roll out to desired thickness for pies and cobblers.
Makes 3 single pie crusts.

title: foolproof gravy
directions: Pour drippings into pan.
Add soup and stir often until desired thickness.

title: beef stroganoff(microwave)
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice into thin, bite-size pieces (strips).
In a 3-quart bowl, toss beef with 1/4 cup flour. Stir in mushrooms, onion, beef broth, ketchup, butter, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook on 100% for 5 minutes; stir.
Reduce to 50%.
Cook, covered, 18 to 33 minutes, stirring half time.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and chill about an hour.

title: cheese ball in a bowl
directions: Soften cheeses if necessary.
Cream until well mixed.
Stir in olives, onion, corned beef and Worcestershire sauce.
Mound in a bowl; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers, raw vegies or whatever you like.

title: muffalettas
directions: Combine olive salad, black olives and celery in a bowl and mix well.
Cut bread in half to form 2 rounds and remove some of the soft inside from each half so that sandwich won't be too thick. Brush inside each half with olive oil mixture.
Spread olive salad mixture over bottom half of bread.
Top with salami, ham, Mortadella and cheeses.
Replace top half of bread and cut sandwich into quarters.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Let Jell-O set slightly before adding the celery, nuts and apples.
Chill until firmly set.
Great for Thanksgiving!

title: spray and wash
directions: Put in a spray bottle or in a detergent bottle and use on "ring around the collar" or other dirty spots.

title: chocolate topped peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then gradually add the milk, beating until well mixed. Fold in the Cool Whip and pour into the pie crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Let boil for 4 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma's frozen salad
directions: Mix all together and place in 9 x 13 inch pan. Cover and place in freezer overnight or up to 3 days. When ready to use, let sit for awhile to slightly thaw. Cut into squares to serve. Looks nice sitting on a large lettuce leaf. Some like to let it thaw completely, but I like mine mostly frozen.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs (beaten).
Add vanilla; stir together with raisins.
Add all dry ingredients: flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal and milk; mix completely. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet in 375°
oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend shortening in flour and salt.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: apple sausage dressing
directions: Dice celery and onion; cook in chicken broth until done.
Mix sausage, apples, cracker crumbs and crumbled corn bread.
Add the onion and celery.
Add the sage the last thing to suit your taste. I bake this separately at 400°.
I make gravy and put some on top of dressing when it is served.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together all 5 dry ingredients into large mixing bowl. Add remaining mayonnaise, warm water and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix and
sift dry ingredients.
Put molasses and shortening in saucepan and heat slowly until shortening is melted and mixed with molasses.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and molasses mixture and dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in well-greased sheet pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve plain or use whipped cream or caramel or lemon sauce. This is delicious.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs in dish with melted butter. Add sugar, then sift flour on top of the sugar.
Beat ingredients well before adding vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until filling is firm and crust is golden brown, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: georgia peaches and cream
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour and butter.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Press into 9x13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Set aside.
Mix confectioners' sugar with cream cheese until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon on top of crust, pushing sides up to make a slight well for peaches.
Set aside.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Combine and mix on low speed until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed (sour cream dissolved).
Chill and serve with fresh strawberries.
Yields 35 ounces.

title: dump cake(quick and easy)
directions: Grease 9x13 cake pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on the bottom, add pineapple with juice.
Sprinkle with cake mix then butter, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well each time.
Ad flour, sifted; add cocoa, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: escalloped corn treat
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
A little margarine poured on top will brown it nicely. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grandma krup's christmas candy cane cookies
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, flavorings and sugars.
Add flour with salt.
Divide dough in half.
Put red food coloring in 1/2 dough. Use a little confectioners sugar and a little flour to make dough less sticky and break into small balls.
Roll out like a stick; do white and red sticks, then twist together.
Put on baking pan. Bake until light brown at 375° (about 9 to 12 minutes).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and hot water.
Let stand, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add butter and beat until fluffy.
Add sugars gradually and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs. Mix well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt stick of butter in square casserole dish.
Combine chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Tear chicken apart and arrange over butter.
Pour mixture of soup over chicken; drain Veg-All and pour over mixture.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Make smooth, then pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Mix all together in a large casserole dish.
Bake, covered, with aluminum foil for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: Cream butter with bananas.
Add nutmeg.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add pineapple (save juice).
Add 2 cups flour alternately with 1 cup juice.
Mix dates, raisins and nuts.
Add to 1 cup flour.
Mix both mixtures thoroughly.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set at 300°.
Bake 2 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: artichoke-chili dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix with drained green chili peppers.
Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture into a 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or bread sticks.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: egg bake dinner
directions: Cut the eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks to a bowl and set the whites aside.
Mash the yolks until they are the consistency of coarse corn meal.
Add the mayonnaise, salt, curry and mustard.
Mix all together well.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set but not brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, sour cream, black pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of Durkee onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Sprinkle jello over drained fruit and let set for 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream and Cool Whip with jello/fruit mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate.
It is best to let this set overnight.

title: pork chop or chicken casserole
directions: Mix in 9 x
13-inch
pan.
Add	chicken
or pork chops. Cover with 1/2 envelope onion soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: deli salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare fresh apples, diced small and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs until creamy with low speed.
Sift flour and measure and sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour at a time and beat well after each addition.
When all flour has been added and batter becomes stiff, remove mixer and fold in nuts and raw apples. Bake in oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread into small pieces.
Add onions, celery, black pepper and sage; mix well.
Add broth or debone chicken enough to moisten well.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together, allowing the children to measure and add the amounts.
Add the oil and water, mixing well. You must wait a few minutes after adding the boiling water before letting the children knead the dough.
This allows plenty of time for everyone to get a chance to stir the mixture.
Knead the dough well and store in a tightly sealed container when finished.
Great fun for all ages!

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt both chocolates in small saucepan over hot water.
Spread 1/4 of mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.
Sprinkle on marshmallows and nuts.
Cover with remaining chocolate spreading evenly.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: scrumptious brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat; stir together sugar and cocoa. Then add to butter; stir.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir again.
Now add flour and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Not too much.
Add walnuts now.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all and put in 9 x 13 casserole.

title: shrimp and dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candy apples
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, combine sugar, corn syrup, food coloring and 1 1/2 cups water.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and liquid comes to a boil.
Set a candy thermometer in mixture.
Temperature reaches 290° about 20 minutes.
Dip apples one by one to coat evenly.
Work quickly.
Place apples on greased sheet.

title: fudge marble brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside cocoa packet.
Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup water, eggs and butter in large bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended. Measure 1/2 cup batter into small bowl.
Add cocoa packet, chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir until blended.
Add nuts to yellow batter.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Quickly brown pork chops in cooking oil; debone.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Add in layers of potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Mix soup with 1 can of water; pour over layers. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread and stir.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake 2 pie shells and let cool.
Place 1 pint of strawberries in each shell.
Combine in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, water, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until thick over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add 1 package of strawberry Jell-O and red food coloring.
Pour over berries.
Place pies in refrigerator before serving.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a deep bowl, shred the head of lettuce.
Add green peppers and onion.
Add peas, then water chestnuts or celery.
Top with salad dressing and then grated cheese and bacon.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine to mix well all ingredients except French dressing and mayonnaise.
Combine dressing and mayonnaise, mixing well, and coat all other ingredients.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Put in three inches of chocolate.
Put in three spoons of sugar.
Add 2 cups flour.
Put in 3 cups of milk.
Put in 4 pieces of ice and mix it up.
Scoop it on a cone when it is frozen.

title: zucchini spice bread
directions: Bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Fry in Pam, uncovered, until brown.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add vanilla, flour and eggs; alternating portions of flour with each egg and mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in olive oil; add onion and cook until tender. Stir in all other ingredients except 3 of the olives and the cheese.
Use the ingredients in the order that they are listed. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer five minutes.
Spoon into a baking dish and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts and top with remaining olive slices.
Double this if you want a large casserole as this only serves 6.

title: white swan inn chocolate-chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Combine both mixtures (best mixed by hand). Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften lard in hot water.
Add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add egg.
Mix well all together and add flour. Beat well.
Place in refrigerator to chill (dough will be soft until it chills).
Make out 1 hour before baking (or enough time to double dough, time depending on temperature of room).
Bake at around 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 or more weeks, using only amount needed.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make a paste by blending cold chicken stock and 1/3 cup flour. Add paste to hot chicken stock and cook over direct heat, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Combine with boned and diced chicken, celery, salt and peas.
Pour into buttered casserole. Sift 1 cup flour, cut into butter or margarine and add milk, stirring with fork until dough stiffens.
Roll on floured board and place over casserole.
Bake in 425° oven about 20 minutes until brown.

title: lickety-split cocoa cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add other ingredients and stir with wire whisk, just until well blended. Bake in greased cake pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peas and peanut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except peanuts. Add shortly before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients and work in lard or shortening.
Beat eggs in cup; add vinegar and fill with water to make 1 cup.
Mix well, after adding liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans. Soak overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts water and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours (until beans are tender).
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor; drain.
Add gelatine and mayonnaise.
Mix and set overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease 1 to 2-quart baking dish liberally with butter.
Cover sides and bottom of buttered dish with half of the Ritz crumbs. Place in layers:
beans, cheese, onion and water chestnuts.
Makes 2 layers.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Top with remaining Ritz cracker crumbs.
Drizzle 3 or 4 tablespoons melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Peel squash.
Grind all vegetables.
Add 5 tablespoons salt. Let stand overnight.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling.
In a large bowl, pour hot water mixture over stuffing mix.
Toss.
Pat 1/2 of stuffing mixture in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Add tomatoes and rice, mixing well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° approximately one hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add the raspberries.
Stir until thawed.
Grate cream cheese. Add to Jell-O mixture.
Add nuts, if wanted.
Chill.

title: maple cream
directions: Prepare an ice bath: fill a large bowl with 1/2-inch water and ice. Pour maple syrup into a small high-sided saucepan, and stir in milk. Set a candy thermometer in the syrup, and place over medium-high heat. Cook, without stirring, until the temperature registers 232 degrees on candy thermometer, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat, and pour into a cold, clean saucepan placed in the ice bath. Do not move or disturb the syrup in any way whatsoever while cooling: If the syrup gets jiggled at this point in the process, the cream won't form. Let stand, adding ice as needed until the syrup radiates a gentle warmth to the back of the hand when held about 1-inch above it or a candy thermometer registers about 100 degrees. Once the mixture reaches the proper temperature, using a wooden spoon, stir slowly until the mixture turns a lighter color and thickens to the consistency of peanut butter, about 12 minutes. Working quickly, transfer the cream to a jar or plastic container, and store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 6 months, or store indefinitely in the freezer.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Mix well the mayonnaise, dressing and olive oil.
Add in the remaining ingredients.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over kraut, peppers, onion and celery.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Remove from refrigerator occasionally and shake.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Spread hash browns over greased 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Melt butter.
Add milk and cheeses.
Stir constantly; don't let boil. Pour over hash browns.
Salt and pepper.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve the jello as usual. Chill until syrup is thick.
Add the pineapple.
Add the marshmallows, bananas and oranges.

title: grandma's emerald salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; cool.
Mix cottage cheese, mayo, salt, pineapple and juice and vinegar.
Stir in jello.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When partially set, sprinkle on 3 tablespoons chopped pecans.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Chop shrimp in blender.
Blend with softened cream cheese and margarine.	Add horseradish and hot sauce to taste.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir
until
mixed.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch
pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: aunt stella's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour and soda. Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix and add ginger ale right before serving.

title: tequila lime punch
directions: Mix all together. Float the lime and orange slices on top. Serve over ice. Makes 24 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses warm to room temperature and mix together well. Add garlic powder and pecans.
Form into a ball.
Garnish with either chili powder or paprika.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in jars.
To serve, fill cup halfway with mixture and add hot water.
Very creamy.
Kids love this.

title: holiday brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured cake roll pan or line pan with aluminum foil.
Bake 25 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Let cool completely in the pan.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Chop velveeta into squares and place in crockpot have heat on high at first then place velveeta and next 5 ingredients.
Cut broccoli tops off and only use the stem.
Place in pot with other ingredients, and when everything is soupy, place heat on low until ready to serve, and enjoy.

title: quick fruit dessert
directions: Mix the 3 cans of fruit with juices together.
Stir
in the dry instant pudding mix.
Refrigerate until set.
Then top with Cool Whip.
When ready to serve, top with maraschino cherries or banana slices or blueberries or coconut, or a combination of any.

title: bonnie's shrimp and scallop scampi
directions: In pan, steam scallops until cooked.
In another pan, cook pasta.
In skillet, melt stick of butter.
When it is all melted, add Italian seasoning and garlic (minced).
Add shrimp and scallops and toss lightly until pasta is fully cooked.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
The longer the better.

title: party green beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Turn into buttered shallow 2-quart casserole and alternate layers of beans, water chestnuts and cheese. (Option:
You can also alternate with 1 (1 pound) can of bean sprouts, drained and rinsed. I don't really like sprouts.)
Prepare cream sauce.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix together the mushroom soup, mayonnaise, beaten eggs, grated cheese and onion.
Add broccoli.
Put in a flat 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put crushed cheese crackers on top.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 350°.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm on top.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cornbread, golden
directions: Put self-rising white or yellow meal in a bowl with self-rising flour.
Stir in egg.
Pour in buttermilk and add salt.
Then add 1 cup of water or until mix is smooth.
Pour into a well-oiled bread pan.
Bake the mix until it turns yellow.
Then turn oven to broil. When crust is light brown or golden, bread is done.

title: chocolate chip squash cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in dry ingredients, then add your oil, eggs and squash.
Mix well and then fold in the chocolate chips.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spanish lima beans
directions: Put onion, garlic, olive oil and thyme in microwavable dish. Cover and cook on High 1 to 2 minutes until onion is crisp-tender. Stir in lima beans.
Cover and cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until heated.
Serves 4.

title: peaches pudding salad
directions: Mix these in pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add immediately 2 cups small marshmallows. Stir until marshmallows are melted, then add 1 large can peaches and juice and refrigerate.

title: ham and cheese brunch bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Line bottom of baking dish with half the sliced bread.
Butter bread. Cover bread with half the ham and cheese.
Repeat.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add milk and beat well.
Pour over top evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salsa
directions: In food processor, mince jalapeno peppers and onions together. Dump into mixing bowl. Process can of tomatoes slightly (tomatoes should be in small chunks, not pureed); add tomatoes to mixing bowl with remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with fork.
After mixed well, store in glass container and refrigerate.
Makes approximately 64 ounces.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add beaten eggs and the rest of buttermilk.
Fold in melted butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, soup, chicken broth and Veg-All in a bowl.
When well mixed, pour into an oblong baking pan.
Mix flour, milk and butter in a bowl.
Pour this mixture on top of the chicken and spread evenly.

title: fruit pie
directions: Drain all fruits.
Combine lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk. Mix until thick.
Add Cool Whip; add fruit, coconut and nuts. Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill until firm.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender and serve.

title: apricot-orange glaze
directions: In microwave-safe glass dish, combine jam and margarine. Microwave on High (100% power) 30 to 60 seconds or until margarine is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Use as a browning glaze for whole turkey or turkey portions.
Yields 19 tablespoons.

title: rachel's ginger spicy chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken.
Cook in oil over medium heat until lightly browned and cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Remove and reserve.

title: whoopie pies(cookies)
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream next four ingredients.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture by hand. Batter should be thick so it doesn't run.
Drop the tablespoon into greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: menudo
directions: Put tripe in a large pan and cover with plenty of water. Bring to a boil and simmer until most of the fat comes to the top. Drain and rinse.
Return to the pot and add onion, chili sauce, tomatoes and a few pinches of oregano.
You may also add the pigs feet at this time.
Cook until tender.
Just before the pigs feet are done, add hominy and bell pepper, if you wish.
Serve with tortillas, chili beans and tossed salad.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Melt both chips over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Fold in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper lined sheet.
Let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: fabulous carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs into sugar, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and blend with oil.
Add to egg and sugar mixture. Fold in carrots and nuts. Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana butter-mallow cake
directions: Bake Banana Yellow Cake in oblong pan.
Cool.
Prepare butterscotch pudding mix (not instant) as directed on package. Spread on top of cake to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Frost with Mallow-Nut Frosting.

title: afternoon tea scones
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add sugar and salt.
Rub in butter.
Add fruit and mix.
Add eggs and sufficient milk to make stiff dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead until surface next to board is smooth.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick and cut into squares or with a cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with butter, jam and whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar, jello and hot water.
Stir until dissolved. Add cranberries, celery, apples and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: creative dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir about 4 minutes or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from saucepan and let stand 5 minutes.
Knead dough about 30 seconds, until smooth and blended.
Cool completely and have fun! Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: carolyn's corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Add chopped bell pepper and onion.
Mix well. Add 1 tablespoon mayonnaise (or enough to suit taste).
Mix well. Let sit, covered, in refrigerator for 24 hours for best flavor. This is a year round favorite!

title: lizzies(rich and delicious)
directions: Stir raisins and bourbon together and let stand 1 hour. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter then gradually beat in brown sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.

title: lamb burger
directions: Gently mix
together
lamb,
green
pepper,
soy sauce, lemon rind and
ginger.
Shape
into 12 patty, slightly larger than the pineapple
slices.	Top
6	of
the
patties
with	a pineapple slice.
Spoon
1 tablespoon of yogurt into center of each.	Top the
pineapple
with another lamb patty.
Pinch the edges together all around to form a large burger.	Grill about 4-inches above heat for
6 to 8 minutes per side or to desired doneness.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except cornstarch mixture, sugar, lemon juice and chicken, in pan.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Taste sauce and adjust seasonings.
Add sugar to taste.
Lemon juice adds a nice zip.
Add cornstarch mixture gradually until sauce reaches desired thickness.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until middle is firm and brown, about 1 hour.

title: toffee candy
directions: Melt butter in skillet over high heat.
Mix in sugar, water and vanilla; stir constantly until tan in color or reaches hard boil stage.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Spread broken up candy bar on top
and mix together until candy bar is melted.
Put into freezer until hard and break into pieces.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix cranberries, orange sections, nuts, crushed pineapple and juice, celery and cooled red raspberry Jell-O.
Chill.
Will freeze okay.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together except 1/2 cup butter and cracker crumbs. Pour crumbs on potatoes, then butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine tomato, onion and garlic. Add lemon juice, salt and chilies. Peel and remove pits from avocados. Mash avocados and combine with other ingredients. Chill and serve with chips.

title: dainty oatmeals
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend. Add oatmeal, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from demitasse spoon 2 inches apart on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes and slide off foil.
Store in cans.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Add sugar and water as required on Kool-Aid package.
Mix all liquids and add raspberry sherbet to float in it.

title: buttery caramel quicks
directions: Preheat oven to 425° in 9-inch square pan.
Melt butter.
Stir in 1/3 cup brown sugar and water.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk all at once, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out onto well-floured surface.
Roll out to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up, starting with 12-inch side.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place cut-side down in prepared pan.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Turn out immediately.
Serve hot.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk and pour over cake and spread.
Cool cake and spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in Crisco.
Add salt and pepper.
Arrange meat and onion in bottom of a heat-resistant glass dish.
Spread corn on top of meat.
Spread fluffy mashed potatoes on top of corn and set in oven at 350°.
Bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are browned.
Garnish with parsley and paprika and serve.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Blend milk and egg in a medium bowl.
Add spaghetti and toss. Spray a 15 x 10-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread spaghetti mixture evenly in the pan.
Cook beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic in a large skillet until beef is just brown. Drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture over spaghetti.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Slowly add sugar syrup to egg whites in a mixer bowl, beating constantly, with electric mixer about 7 minutes or until it forms stiff peaks. Beat in vanilla.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix powdered jello with rest of items.
Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine shortening and scalded milk; stir until shortening is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt and beat in cold water. Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine the three mixtures and add flour.
Cover and chill overnight.
Shape; let rise and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: au gratin hash browns
directions: Let potatoes stand until they can be separated.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 3-quart casserole.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and eat. Makes 6 servings.

title: goooood banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Eagle Brand milk until thickened. Fold in 13 ounce Cool Whip to this.
Line pan with bananas and alternate
bananas	and
vanilla
wafers, top
with Cool Whip. Pineapple
may
be	used instead of bananas or combinations of both.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Ground up ground beef and chop the onion.
Fry both together until brown.
When done, slowly pour Ragu sauce in while stirring. Simmer until warm.
In casserole dish, simmer until warm.
In casserole dish, put layer of noodles, sauce mixture, then cheese until casserole dish is full.
The final layer should be noodles topped with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add applesauce.
Blend in flour, cocoa, soda and spices.
Add pineapple, raisin and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except butter and pecans. Pour into baking dish. Top with butter and pecans. Bake 30 minutes at 325°. Serve with rye bread or Triscuits.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: araiana's apple pancakes
directions: Beat in large bowl the milk, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Heat your pancake griddle or grease a large frypan on medium heat.
Pour 1/4 of batter for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form.
Turn over.
Cook until golden.
Serve with syrup.

title: easy strawberry trifle
directions: Cut each jelly roll into 3 slices; arrange cut sides of slices around sides and bottom of a 2 1/2-quart souffl or trifle dish. Fill in with remaining slices. Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, using 1 1/2 cups milk; let stand 5 minutes. Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.

title: southern tea punch
directions: Bring 1 quart water to a boil. Remove from heat. Add tea bags. Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags. Combine tea and remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve punch over ice.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Pour rest of batter on top.
Sprinkle rest of mix over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Beat together all ingredients (except wafers) until smooth and creamy.
Put cupcake papers in cupcake tins and place a whole wafer
at bottom.
Fill 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine pumpkin pie mix, nut bread mix and egg; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into greased medium size muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields about 30.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, brown meat with chopped onion.
Drain off all fat, then add the cans of tomatoes, paste and water.
Cover top of sauce with the oregano, Italian herb seasoning, basil leaves, thyme and garlic salt to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add the bay leaf.
Cook slowly until very thick.

title: slaw
directions: Shred and chop first 4 ingredients.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Let cool and pour over slaw mixture.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Blend all ingredients and simmer as desired.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Place one roll of crescent rolls in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, and vanilla together and spread on top of rolls.
Add blueberries (or selected fruit of your choice), and top with the second roll of crescent rolls.
(I roll these out on my pastry sheet to seam the rolls together and to enlarge it slightly.)
Crimp the edges of the two crust layers together.
Beat one egg white until frothy and brush on top. Sprinkle with chopped pecans and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cheese pastries
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add flour using a wooden spoon.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill overnight and next day, flatten balls out with palm of hand on waxed paper forming a circle.
Fill center with raspberry preserves and finely chopped nuts.
Fold in half and pinch together.
Dot with milk.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, aluminum foil-lined.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: green chili sauce
directions: Dice pork roast and fry until brown.
Add flour and water to make gravy.
Dice green chili, tomato and garlic.
Add diced jalapenos and 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on medium about 5 hours.
Add salt and pepper during cooking time.
Serve over burritos or with tortillas.

title: white trash
directions: Melt the butter and peanut butter together.
Pour into a large bowl adding the rest of the ingredients, except powdered sugar. Pour the powdered sugar over top.
Place top on bowl and shake well to coat.

title: lacy-thin hoe cake
directions: Put oil on a round iron griddle and heat on high to get griddle hot, then put on low heat.
Mix just enough water with cornmeal to make it soupy thick to pour on a hot griddle.
Pour a thin layer of batter on griddle and cook slowly.

title: light-as-a-feather gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon and cloves into large bowl.
Stir in enough oil to make mixture crumbly.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine molasses and boiling water in bowl; mix well.
Add 3/4 cup molasses mixture to flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Add remaining molasses mixture, stirring just until well mixed.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until gingerbread tests done.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and
corn
syrup together well.
Then add the butter, eggs, flavoring
and
pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana daiquiris
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend on high speed until foamy.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer boiled chicken and Pepperidge Farm mix.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and dressing.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and put in 2 baked pie shells and chill before serving.

title: spiced cranberry punch (hot)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain cider, discarding spices and lemon.
Serve.

title: venison cube steak
directions: Soak deer cubes in 2 cups of milk or enough to cover meat overnight or at least 1 hour before cooking.
(Optional:
Or spread both sides with mustard just before deep frying.)
Mix flour and spices.
Shake in large storage bag.
Deep fry until at a "float" stage.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in a greased large Bundt pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon together and pour over rolls. Layer one at a time, chopped nuts and pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around rolls.
Cover with with cloth. Let set on counter overnight. Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Invert pan over large serving dish.
Let set a few minutes so syrup will cover rolls. Serve hot.
These are delicious and very easy!!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel potatoes (works well under cold, running water).
Mash potatoes well until lumps are out. Add butter and sugar to hot potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat briefly until well mixed.
Pour into prebaked frozen pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add zucchini, dry ingredients and nuts alternately. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: brown rice and pork casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before dinner, heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from chops and heat in skillet.
Sprinkle chops well with seasoned salt; brown both sides well in hot skillet, remove to 2-quart casserole.
Add rice to drippings in skillet and cook, stirring until brown.
Stir in gravy or soup, water, salt and pepper. Arrange onions and carrots on top of chops.
Pour on gravy mix. Bake uncovered 1 hour or until chops and vegetables are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all of the moisture out of the spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cheese in microwave.
Mix in crab, milk, sauce and onion.
Heat and serve hot.
For best results, make a day ahead and refrigerate.

title: quick filled coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter in a bowl until creamy. Add 1 cup sugar and mix thoroughly. Add egg yolks and beat well. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add to butter mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into batter. Pour about 2/3 of the mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam nonstick spray.
Pour ingredients into Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake mix and 1 egg.
Press the mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and the remaining eggs.
Pour this mixture over the top of the mixture in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bars and enjoy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Melt butter.
Cool.
Beat eggs, sugar and butter together. Add flour, milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie plates. Crust forms as it bakes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crock pot chicken-fried chops
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine flour, ground mustard, salt and garlic powder and dredge pork chops.
In a skillet, brown both sides in oil.
Place in greased crock pot.
Combine soup and water until smooth; pour over chops.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: potato soup with sweet onions
directions: In a large pot, boil potatoes and onion with water.
Cover pot and boil 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
In a large skillet, melt butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Simmer and gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Add flour mixture to potatoes and onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle chives on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cut the peanut butter and powdered sugar together; this will not be smooth.
Sprinkle some over crust, then pour custard into crust and sprinkle rest of peanut butter and sugar mixture over the custard.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple cooler
directions: Mix juices and frozen orange juice; chill.
Add chilled club soda immediately before serving.
Serve over ice in tall glasses. Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken and broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion and celery in butter over medium heat until softened.
Add flour and stir until completely blended. Stir in milk, bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to low boil.
Stir in chicken and broccoli; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Season with pepper.

title: french vanilla trifle
directions: Thaw frozen fruit.
Cut pound cake in 1/2-inch pieces; put aside.
Layer pound cake, thawed fruit and pudding in trifle container.
Repeat layering and top with whipped topping. Refrigerate and serve.

title: southern-style sausage dressing
directions: Saute sausage, celery and onion. In large bowl, combine sausage mixture and remaining ingredients; blend well. Stuff mixture into bird and roast according to standard roasting directions. Mixture may also be baked in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned. Makes about 12 cups or 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cake mix.
In a large bowl, mix remaining cake mix, 1/2 cup butter and 1 egg until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: the giant's spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Add Bleu cheese in crumbled chunks.
(Chunks will break up when stirred in.)
Stir Bleu cheese into mixture.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Drain tamales, unwrap and cut into slices.
Place slices in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
End with cheese and crushed chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly throughout (approximately 30 minutes).
Serve with choice of Mexican condiments, such as: shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped onion, salsa and sour cream.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and margarine.
Mix well with a spoon.
Fold in nuts.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet about the size of a half-dollar.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly brown.
Remove cookies with a metal spatula and cool before serving.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Dip fingers into water, then sugar and flatten balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: creamy pumpkin dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices. Place in rows in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press to corners and edges.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Heat cranberry juice, sugar and water in a large pot.
Heat on low.
Put red hots candy in the microwave with some of the liquid and microwave until candy is dissolved.
Add to juice mixture.
Turn heat off and add lemonade and orange juice.
This will make a good bit of concentrated tea.
Dilute to taste when you are ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and add cream, cheese and milk.
Boil slow.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in 1-quart casserole and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in pineapple and spread in pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple and pie filling.
Cut margarine in patties and place evenly over batter.
(Don't mix.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost if desired.

title: cream of potato soup i
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onions until tender; mash up fine. Mix sour cream with flour until smooth.
Add to soup.
Add 2 cups very hot milk; stir constantly until thick.

title: crab puffs
directions: Soften margarine and cheese.
Mix in other ingredients and add crab meat.
Spread mixture on muffins (cut in half).
Then cut each muffin into 6 sections.
Broil until crisp (5 to 8 minutes). Puffs may be frozen before broiling.
They line up by the stove for this one!

title: hungry boy casserole(hamburger and beans topped with meat-filled biscuits.)
directions: Saute in skillet, beef (reserve 1/2 pound cooked for biscuits), celery, onions, green pepper and garlic until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add water, tomato paste, salt, beans and peas.
Simmer.
Prepare biscuits.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash 3 bananas.
Mix all ingredients and put in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put some brown sugar on top.

title: rebbeca's strawberry cake
directions: Cook yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Cook in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Slice cake 1/2 in middle of cake to make 2 layers. Drain strawberries.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and sugar.
Fold in the drained strawberries.
Half of mixture between layers and 1/2 on top of cake.
Prepare 1 day ahead before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: low-fat oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. In large mixer bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar, butter and applesauce until smooth.
Beat in egg whites and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 or 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 or 13 minutes to a crisp cookie.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets; cool on wire racks.

title: lime salad
directions: Blend well and pour in mold rubbed with mayonnaise.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into 1/4 cup water, add salt, sugar and butter (softened).
Stir well.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) and milk.
Add flour a little at a time until dough feels soft and velvety.
Knead well, place in large bowl, cover and let rise until double (or about 1 1/2 hours).
Knead well and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Knead well and roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread dough with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll up and slice into 1 1/2 inch slices.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.
Mix 1/4 cup milk, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Brush cinnamon rolls with icing while hot.

title: 4-layer cake
directions: Cream together margarine, flour and pecans.
Mix together and bake in shallow 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: penny carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Mix well.
Add onion and peppers.
Mix well.
Bring mixture to boiling point, stirring frequently.
Place carrots in a glass bowl.
Pour tomato mixture over carrots.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator for at least 2 days.
Mixture may be stored in refrigerator 2 or 3 weeks.

title: whole wheat bran bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add
brown
sugar, salt, hot water, shortening, whole wheat flour, bran and 1 cup bread flour. Beat
at medium speed for 3
minutes.
Add
remaining flour gradually to form a stiff dough and
knead
until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in greased bowl,
covered
loosely with plastic.
When doubled in size, punch down and
let
rest
10 minutes.
Place in 2 greased bread pans and bake
at
375° for 30 minutes.
Reduce
heat
to 350° and bake 10
to
more minutes.

title: lemon tea cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Set aside.
Cream oleo and sugars in large mixing bowl.
Blend in oil, eggs, lemon peel and lemon extract.
Stir in flour mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls(double batch)
directions: Mix butter, graham crackers, coconut, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and chill again for 2 hours.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Prepare and slice mushrooms.
Saute them in fat until done. Then add them to the white sauce.
Season with salt and lemon juice.
Add egg yolk, beaten with water or stir in cream.

title: microwave marble fudge
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch pieces and peanut butter in a large glass bowl.
Microwave on Medium for about 5 minutes.
Stir until melted and mixed.
Fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for several hours or until firm and set.
Cut into squares.

title: ham and potato chowder
directions: Saute the chopped
onions,
ham
and
chopped celery in melted butter.
Add the diced potatoes and cook for 15 minutes longer. Remove from heat
and add the salt, pepper, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Return
to heat and warm slowly.
Do not let the soup boil. More milk may be added to thin the soup.
This is a basic recipe and
more
may
be added.
Examples:
1 can corn, fresh mushrooms, carrots...

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the cherry pie filling.
Spread pineapple on top. Spread cake mix on top.
Next put margarine evenly over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and then nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 90 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a large roasting or baking pan and set aside.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt in a saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn; toss to coat well .
Bake at 250° for 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool, break apart and store in an airtight container.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into walnut size balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll flat for deep fried pies.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Fold in apples; then 3/4 of chopped snickers.
Use remainder for topping.
Double recipe if needed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together and drain well.
Mix drained squash and onion with rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients; tossing gently.
Line salad plates with lettuce leaves; spoon fruit mixture on lettuce.
Place a banana half on each side of fruit mixture; sprinkle with coconut, and top with a cherry.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake in a 9 x 3 x 2-inch pan as directed.
When cool, punch holes in cake and spread a large can crushed pineapple (juice and all).
Make a large package of vanilla instant pudding and combine with 8 ounces softened cream cheese and spread on top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: smothered okra
directions: In a covered saucepan, smother okra in oil for 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add onion, bell pepper, tomato and seasoning.
Cook for 30 minutes and add tomato paste. Cook for 15 more minutes.
Ham may be added for flavor.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice about 1/4-inch thickness.
Mix together eggs beaten with a fork and add a little water or milk, salt and pepper to taste and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Fill a dish with flour.
Dip eggplant in flour, then in egg mixture and fry in oil until lightly browned.
Then put on paper towel to absorb excess grease.
Put tomato sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and layer eggplant, then grated or sliced Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and keep repeating layering until all used up.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Remove foil last 10 minutes.

title: corn soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan; set aside.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until blended.
Add soup mixture, corn, salt and pepper to onion mixture, stirring well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Yields 4 cups.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground meat, drain.
Add taco mix and water; cook according to package directions.
Arrange crescent rolls in pie pan and press together to form a crust.
Add 1/2 cup crushed Doritos, then add meat mixture. Spread sour cream over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over pie, then another 1/2 cup of crushed Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust browns and cheese melts.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix together in a long cake pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: continental hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate is melted and blended with water.
Add Imperial sugar and salt; bring to boil and cool.
Add vanilla.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons chocolate mixture to each cup; add hot milk to fill, blend. Top with whipped cream.
If demitasse cups are used, put 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture in each cup and proceed as above. Makes 8 to 12 regular size servings.

title: green chillies casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in large frypan.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mocha chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix egg yolks and confectioners sugar until blended.
Cream butter; add sugar mixture, coffee beans, boiled water and vodka or rum.
Slice Sara Lee pound cake in 5 layers.
Spread mixture on all layers, except top.
Spread top with milk, mixed into melted chocolate chips.

title: bigmama's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together first.
Then add some flour, a tablespoon of orange juice and an egg.
Alternate this until all is mixed well.
Then add flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into cake pan that is well greased.
Cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°. Butter-flavored Crisco is best for this cake.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts, barely covered in water, until done. Take meat off bone and cut into bite size pieces.
In a large bowl, mix broth from chicken, soup, sour cream and chicken together.
Place in casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top and drizzle melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until it bubbles and crackers are browned.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate strawberry cooler
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar, cocoa and half of the milk in blender container; blend well.
Add remaining milk and carbonated beverage; blend.
Garnish with dollop of whipped cream or ice cream and a strawberry, if desired.
Yields two 8-ounce servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add all ingredients.
Depending on the can of corn, you can add 1 tablespoon of milk for consistency.
Drop 1/2 to 1 small teaspoon of the mixture into hot fish grease.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with dry bread crumbs.
Dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until beef is brown and onion is tender. Sprinkle seasonings over this.
Mix undrained tomatoes, beans, rice, water and green pepper with meat mixture.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and cover with cheese. Cover with foil and heat until cheese melts.
May sprinkle crushed Fritos corn chips on top.
Will serve 6 generously.
Bake at 375°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Separate eggs and reserve egg whites for meringue.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook slowly until like jelly.
Bake pie shell.
Put mixture in pie shell and cover with meringue made from the egg whites.

title: mattie albritton chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, eggs, flour and milk in top of double boiler.
(May use thick saucepan on low heat, stirring frequently.)
Cook until thickened.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Add meringue to top and brown slightly.
Let cool and serve.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly and remove 1 cup of mixture to use as the topping.
Set aside.
Add 4 remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkling on topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: banana eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with milk.
Mash bananas through foodmill or blender.
Add egg-milk mixture, salt and nutmeg.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add to banana mixture and beat until frothy.
Serve immediately.
Yields four (8 ounce) servings.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
For filling, beat cream cheese, 1 1/2 c. sugar, eggs and flour until very creamy.
Stir in pumpkin, cinnamon, vanilla, lemon peel, ginger and nutmeg.
Mix until smooth and pour into well greased crust lined spring form pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. For your cream topping, mix sour cream, 4 tbsp. sugar, and flavoring and pour over cheese pie while pie is still hot.
Chill for at least four hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing.
Layer 1/2 on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix first 6 ingredients and spoon over stuffing.
Layer remaining 1/2 stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Roll in cinnamon or put cinnamon in baggie and shake.

title: hard sauce(serve cold to top hot dessert)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add water and salt. Beat.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add corn, oil and sour cream.
Beat well, then add meal.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti meat dish
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic.
Add beef and cook 30 minutes or until done.
Add tomatoes, olives, salt and cheese.
Cook covered over slow heat 30 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and soup.
Mix well with cooked spaghetti.
Put in covered dish and leave in refrigerator overnight or until ready to cook.
You may wish to place in 2 smaller casseroles and freeze one.

title: peach jello mold
directions: Drain fruit, saving juice. Add enough water to juice to make 5 cups. Heat liquid to boiling; dissolve jello. Pour into blender; add cream cheese and fruit. Blend all together and pour into jello mold; refrigerate. Serves 6.

title: royal seafood casserole
directions: Blend soup and mayonnaise in a large bowl; add onion, then milk.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add the remaining ingredients. Turn into a large, shallow buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and scatter slivered almonds generously over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 10.

title: red-skinned potato salad
directions: Wash and scrub the potatoes. Cut each potato into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes. Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and cook about 20 minutes or until tender but still firm. Remove from heat and drain thoroughly. Cool and place in a large serving bowl. Add the celery and chives to the cooled potatoes.

title: natalie's stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry in wok or large (no stick) pan until vegetables are done, but not too soft, in about 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add your shrimp, scallops or imitation crab meat; stir-fry
another 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, syrup and milk and cook.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball.
Add vanilla, pecans and butter.
Stir until smooth; drop onto wax paper.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, with mixer at medium speed.
Reduce speed and add dry ingredients that have been sifted together, alternately with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Grease 8-inch tube pan.
Put 1/3 batter in pan, then swirl 1/3 cranberry. Repeat 2 more times.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool for 5 to 8 minutes.
Then remove from pan. Frost cake while warm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites; gently stir in pecans and coconut.

title: cheesy chowder(good)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water. Add potatoes, vegetables and onion. Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat until cheese spread is melted and all is hot. Yields 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease lightly a 1-quart baking dish.
Layer the bottom with 1/2 of beans and 1/2 of onion rings sprinkled over beans.
Spread the other half of beans over onions, finishing up with onion rings on top.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 3 finger biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Blend biscuit mix and milk; stir well.
Turn onto surface sprinkled with baking mix and form a ball.
Knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with sharp 2-inch cutter without twisting and place close together on baking sheet.
Let rise a few minutes. Then with 3 fingers, pat biscuits down.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes. Brush tops with melted butter or margarine before baking or after. Yields 18 biscuits.

title: cherie's burritos
directions: Brown ground round and onion.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Stir in picante sauce.
Stir in pinto beans.
Add refried beans and stir well.
Cook until thickened and cool slightly.
Place approximately 1/2 to 2/3 cup of mixture on each burrito wrapper. Sprinkle with some grated Cheddar and Monterey Jack.
Roll and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with taco sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 large burritos.

title: baked potato skins
directions: In preheated 425° oven, bake potatoes for 1 hour or until done. Cut each potato in lengthwise quarters.
Scoop out all but 1/4-inch of insides of each potato wedge.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry potato wedges for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Drain well.
Arrange wedges on heatproof dish.
Sprinkle each wedge with about 1 teaspoon crumbled bacon and 2 teaspoons cheese.
Run under broiler to melt cheese.
Serve with sour cream.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift first 8 ingredients together.
Add margarine, water, walnuts, raisins, applesauce and egg; beat about 3 minutes with mixer.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple and cornstarch together until thick. Add jello.
Cool.
Add pecans and bananas and stir.
Put in crusts. Top with Cool Whip.

title: gelatin punch
directions: Mix sugar and gelatin together.
Add hot water to mixture; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and cold water.
Refrigerate until needed.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add the cold Sprite.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and prepare potatoes, as if making mashed potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except 1 tablespoon margarine after mashing potatoes.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil.
Chill up to 24 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie shell 1 hour at 350°.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake crust for 6 minutes, just long enough to set it but not brown it.
Set aside and let cool. Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Slice enough onions to nearly fill the crust.
Saut onions in butter.
In a bowl, combine eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Add onions, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes at 450°, then reduce oven temperature to 325°, baking another 20 minutes.

title: hot and spicy cornmush
directions: Boil water and add uncooked sausage.
Add spices.
Add cornmeal to boiling mixture.
Turn heat to medium.
Add cornmeal until "thick" texture.
Remove from heat and place in loaf pan and refrigerate until firm.
Slice thin and fry until golden brown.

title: chili chicken dinner
directions: Spread chicken parts on a cookie sheet, skin side down. Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Sprinkle garlic powder, salt, pepper and heavy on the chili powder.
Place in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn over, repeat process, return to oven additional 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cornbread and butter; reserve enough to make a layer on top of casserole.
Mix all other ingredients together; pour into casserole dish, topping with cornbread layer.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400° (covered).

title: french birds
directions: Pound steaks thin.
Place a mound of mixture of green onions, bacon, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic in the center of each slice of steak.
Fold steak over stuffing and fasten with toothpicks to seal stuffing inside steak.
Season and roll birds in flour. Brown in oil on all sides.
Use heavy Dutch oven or large black skillet. Add water and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Leftover seasoning may be simmered in gravy.
I always chop a little extra seasonings for this purpose. Serve on rice.

title: 1969 apricot pineapple bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix fruit juice, milk, eggs and fat.
Add fruit to dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 liquid ingredients and stir for 2 minutes.
Add other half and stir for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-oiled loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: marian's dip for fruit
directions: Mix dry Jell-O mix and yogurt. Add Cool Whip. Serve with any fresh fruit (strawberries, oranges, bananas, apples, etc.).

title: taco salad
directions: Fry all ingredients until the meat is brown.
Get some taco chips, lettuce, tomatoes and Cheez Whiz.
Mix all together for taco salad.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cut the crust off the top, bottom and sides of loaf.
Make 8 crosswise cuts in the loaf, dividing it into 9 equal pieces.
Cut about 3/4 of the way through the loaf, not cutting through the bottom.
Make 1 lengthwise cut through the center of the loaf, not cutting through the bottom.

title: hominy cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add onion, salt, chili powder and pepper. Slowly stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Wash and drain hominy; stir into sauce.
Pour into 1-1/2 qt. casserole.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 325° 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade, combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Blend 30 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: watergate saladusa
directions: Pour all ingredients into a large bowl, mix well and refrigerate!! Tastes even better the next day...if there's any left!!

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well. Place in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Toss well.

title: steamed sand dabs
directions: Place sliced bean cake in shallow platter for steaming.
Place the sand dabs on top of the bean cake slices.
Mix the ginger with the bean sauce, then smear on the sand dabs.
Salt and add a few drops of soy sauce.

title: baked stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven at 425° for 45 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Spoon out 1/4-inch from shell.
Place in bowl and mash.
Add butter, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk to taste. Whip.
Return to shells and refrigerate.
Heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden harvest casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and garlic together.
Place in a shallow baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle parsley and grind pepper over all.
At this point, you can refrigerate until ready to bake. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour bouillon into a small saucepan; add oil, salt, tarragon and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; correct seasonings.
Pour over vegetables.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Add other desired vegetables.

title: carob treats
directions: Soften dates over low heat.
Stir.
Add raisins.
Heat until pasty.
Add carob and stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add seeds and coconut.
(Mixture will be stiff.) Spread into a 5 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: holiday leftovers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange turkey in baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Top with broccoli; cover with cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg until foamy. Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and add to wet.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Bake in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: First mix lukewarm water and yeast, then combine all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be kept up to 1 week and used as needed.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar; mix until smooth and blended.
Spread over salad; top with pecans.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Top each chicken breast with 1/2 slice of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Add crumbs; drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat together eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, 1 teaspoon baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to egg mixture alternately with 1 cup of buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in prunes and nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove from and place on a wire rack.
Set over a sheet of wax paper.
With the handle of a wooden spoon, poke holes in through top of cake spacing holes 2 inches apart.

title: swiss cheese sauce
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
(If necessary, beat smooth with rotary beater.)
Mix in sour cream; beat.
Dash with paprika. Serve with hot cauliflower or asparagus.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hot reuben dip
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350° in uncovered casserole. Serve with any crackers, rye bread or bagel chips.

title: beans and wieners
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Combine beans, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar in baking dish.
Fry bacon.
Slice wieners crosswise. Fry wieners in bacon grease.
Add wieners and crumbled bacon to beans; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until heated through.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise or salad dressing and dry Ranch dressing mix.
Mix chopped vegetables into cream cheese mixture and spread over cooled crescent rolls.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar and Mozzarella.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix well.
Cook until thickened.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain and press out as much water as possible.
Melt oleo and beat eggs slightly.
Add chopped onion and eggs to melted oleo.
Add cheese; mix well.
Add spinach and stuffing mix.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Form into balls (about 1 1/2-inch).
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes until lightly browned on bottom, at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
