directions: First day, cube 3 slices trimmed bread in bottom of pan.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, pepper, mayonnaise and spices.
Spread on top of cubed bread.
Refrigerate.
Second day, mix beaten eggs, milk and soup.
Pour over chicken and bread.
Cube remaining bread and lay on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, put on the cheese.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserved liquid to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Layer beets and onion rings in glass bowl.
Pour liquid over them. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lobster, shrimp or crab meat mousse
directions: Heat soup in a saucepan.
Add cream cheese, celery, green peppers and onions.
Dissolve gelatine in water and add.
Heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add lobster, or shrimp or crab meat and seasonings.
Pour into a greased ring mold.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine yogurt with lemon juice, red wine vinegar, oregano and ground cumin.
Mix thoroughly.
Add dressing to salad and toss.
Adjust seasoning.
Eat salad as is or piled in warm pita breads.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in a bowl.
Add water to dissolved yeast.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening. Gradually add flour and mix with hand to make dough.
Place in an icebox overnight.
Cut dough in half.
Roll out like pie crust; thin cut into 16 pie-shaped pieces.
Spread with butter.
Roll from large end.
Put small end down to pan.
May use muffin tins, also. Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until brown.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: norwegian parsley potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
With a sharp knife, remove one narrow strip of skin around the middle of each potato.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add parsley and marjoram.
Add potatoes and stir gently until coated and heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and pour in an air tight container.
Use 2 teaspoons per 1 cup hot water.

title: great corn dish
directions: Beat the egg in a bowl.
Add both cans of corn.
Add sugar and flour and mix well.
In baking dish, melt the stick of butter and pour on top of corn mixture.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers on top to cover and form a crusty top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over roast.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour barbecue sauce over roast. Cook on low.
Every 2 or 3 hours pour off excess grease.
Repeat until fat is cooked away.
Total cooking time:
8 to 12 hours.

title: rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, salt and pepper.
Cook rice until tender.
Place rice and 5 cups of water in roasting pan.
Add the mushroom (or any cream soup) soup and chicken and rice soup.
Mix everything together.
Add soy sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until slightly dry.
(You can use all white rice instead of 1/2 white and 1/2 wild rice.)

title: oriental broccoli salad
directions: Break up Ramen noodles and put in large bowl with broccoli slaw.
In separate bowl, add oil, sugar, vinegar and flavor package from noodles.
Mix well.
Roast almonds on tray in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put dressing on slaw 4 hours before serving and stir and toss.
Put almonds and sunflower seed on slaw just before serving. Stir well and enjoy!

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke chicken salad
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In saucepan, place chicken.
Add water to a depth of about 1/2 inch.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until done.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: rachel's pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add extract.
Mix with flour and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: jamaican rum cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet and set aside.
In large bowl, cream together the rum, butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; then add to the rum-butter mixture.
Blend in the raisins and nuts.
Drop 1 teaspoon of the mixture at a time onto the prepared baking sheet. Allow for considerable spreading.
Bake until brown, about 10 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.
Let cool on a wire rack before serving or store in an airtight container to improve the flavor.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies(soft and moist on the inside and crisp on the outside.)
directions: Simmer raisins and water in saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in raisin liquid.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; stir in.
Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: liver soup
directions: Cook soup bones to make broth.
Add onions, celery, salt, pepper, etc. to taste.
Grind liver in meat grinder.
Add a little salt and pepper and enough flour to hold it together. Strain the soup broth. Return to pan and bring to boil.
Drop by teaspoon little dumplings of the ground liver into the broth and cook until done.
If you like, you may add rice or noodles.
We like the rice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 375° until crust is golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well. Chill for 4 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add corn and flour.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Set in a pan of water and bake 1 hour at 350° until a knife comes out clean.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 2 cups of water and sugar for 10 minutes; cool and add crushed fruit and fruit juice.
Chill.
Add charged water before serving.
This serves 25 persons.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together and bake at temperature given for cake mix used.

title: ritty cracker pie
directions: Add dry ingredients to egg whites and fold in.
Spread in greased pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: quick wheat rolls
directions: Put butter in hot water.
Set aside until butter is slightly melted.
Stir together yeast, 1 cup white flour, honey, salt and powdered milk.
Add water and butter.

title: grandma b's ice cream topping
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Microwave for 20 seconds.
Mix well and microwave for 20 seconds.
Mix well and enjoy on ice cream or the way it is.
Makes one serving.

title: artichokes stuffed with red pepper vinaigrette
directions: Remove artichoke stems and discard.
Break off tough outer leaves and cut off top fourth of artichokes.
Snip off tips of leaves with scissors and rub cut edges with lemon half.

title: open house punch
directions: Refrigerate all ingredients, except Southern Comfort, making sure the orange juice and lemonade are thawed.

title: old time chocolate cake
directions: Put all this in large mixing bowl.
Put soda in buttermilk and stir well.
Pour this on top of other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in 8 x 10-inch cake pan.
Bake until toothpick or fork comes out clean.

title: howard's tofu loaf
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In a medium saucepan, boil tofu for 15 minutes.
Drain well and place in bowl and mash.
Add chestnuts, crab, mayonnaise, eggs, shiitake, carrots and green onions.
Mix well.
Place into greased loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes. Remove pan from oven and pour cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) over loaf.
Cover with foil and place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Freeze.

title: baby sandwiches
directions: Slice hot dog into little round slices and warm in the microwave for 15 seconds.
Put hot dog slices between crackers to make sandwiches.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; set aside. Melt butter; add onions and pepper. Cook. Blend flour, sugar and salt; add milk. Cook over low heat; stir in vinegar and mustard. Pour over potatoes and toss lightly. Put paprika on top.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt until dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers, celery and onion, then put in glass jars.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, then put in containers and freeze.
I sometimes omit some of the cucumbers and add cauliflower.

title: frozen island salad
directions: Thoroughly blend yogurt into softened cream cheese.
Stir in sugar and pineapple, blending well.
Line a muffin pan with 6 paper baking cups.
Spoon mixture into cups, cover and freeze.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Mix in crab.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corn well; pour into casserole dish.
Beat eggs, then add can milk, salt and sugar.
Pour over corn; dot with a tablespoon of butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour (until blade of knife comes out clean.)

title: authentic scotch broth
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine lamb shanks, barley, salt, parsley, cloves, bay leaf and 5 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 1 hour. Remove shanks from soup.
Remove meat from bones; discard bones. Cut meat into pieces; return to soup.
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and cloves.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix together margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat out on 12-inch pizza pan.
Brown in oven at 250° until brown (about 35 to 40 minutes).
Let cool completely.

title: coffee dough
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl, making a well in center.
Stir coffee into water in a cup.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients, stir thoroughly.
Add more flour or water, as needed.
Knead until smooth on lightly floured board, about 5 minutes.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.
Model with it (1/2 inch thick if you plan to bake it).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until hard, on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Varnish cooled project to seal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and the milk until slightly thickened. Add to this mixture the Cool Whip. Put in crust and refrigerate.

title: quickie coffee cake
directions: Separate biscuits.
Crush cornflakes into fine crumbs. Combine with cinnamon.
Beat honey and butter together.
Dip biscuits in honey and butter mixture, then into crumb mixture. Overlap biscuits in greased 3-cup ring mold. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Place on warm serving plate.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package, drain.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form spaghetti into a 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage or Ricotta cheese over bottom of crust.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake until melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gift giving carrot cakes
directions: Grease and flour 6 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) loaf pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat eggs, sugar, mayonnaise, pineapple and 1/2 cup juice until well blended.
Beat in flour mixture until well mixed.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: penne with olive-tomato sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium to low heat and saute onion about 3 minutes.
Add anchovy and garlic and cook, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and red pepper flakes.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Add olives and black pepper.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Transfer to shallow bowl.
Top with sauce and stir to blend.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Heat chicken or mushroom soup with about 1/3 can of milk. Remove from heat.
Add mayonnaise.
Cook broccoli about 5 minutes. Mix all ingredients in a baking dish, reserving a few noodles to put on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
mix
flour, cornmeal, baking soda, sugar and
salt.
With pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in shredded cheese, vinegar and cold water just until mixture forms a soft dough. Shape
into a ball, wrap with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.
(Or place dough in freezer for 30 minutes.)

title: chess cake
directions: Blend together eggs, confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Pour this over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato paste and sauce; simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Spoon mixture into greased baking dish.
Separate each biscuit into 2 pieces.
Place biscuits near outer edge, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese in center.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Brush biscuits with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 c. soup, ground beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and salt.
Press mixture into a 9 inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Mix remaining soup with mashed potatoes and frost the meat loaf. Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Bake 10 - 15 minutes longer.

title: creamy pork chops
directions: Brown chops, season and drain fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: momma's #1 sauce
directions: Pour 1/2 cup oil in large cooking pot along with onion and garlic.
Let fry until onion gets golden.
Pour in tomato paste and peeled tomatoes and stir.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and basil and cook for 1 hour or so until oil flows to top of sauce.

title: hamburger salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain and cool.
Add chopped tomatoes, onions, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients with mayo or Miracle Whip.
This is especially great with pinto beans or peas.

title: salsa chocolata
directions: Stir until melted and no lumps.
Serve over ice cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Cream oleo and sugar well; add egg yolks.
Beat until mixture turns a lighter color and fluffy.
Add soda to sour cream; alternate with flour to the sugar mixture. Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Gently fold into cake batter. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven, 300° to 325°, for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 1/2 hours until cake springs to touch.
Turn out on cooling rack to cool.

title: pork chops en casserole
directions: Trim off excess fat from pork chops.
Roll them in mixture of bread crumbs, salt, pepper, sage and curry powder.
Saute in hot oil in skillet until brown.
Remove from skillet and place chops in casserole.
Top with green pepper and onions.
Pour tomato puree or sauce over.
Cook in a slow oven, 300°, for 2 hours.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Wash the squash and cut off both ends.
Cook in small amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain.
When cooled, cut in halves lengthwise and scoop out the center.
Combine centers of squash, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and egg; mix thoroughly. Fill squash shells with mixture and place stuffed squash on a shallow pan.
Sprinkle tops with grated cheese.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted and filling is heated thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: graham cracker chew
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Grease
a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at
for
approximately
30 minutes until it lightly springs up.
Cut in small squares while warm.

title: vegetarian nut roast
directions: Saute in water and oil, celery and onions.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Place in lightly oiled loaf pan and bake at 350°. Loaf may have to be covered with tinfoil near end of baking if top begins to get too brown.
Good served with gravy.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add oil, egg yolks, water, coconut and orange rind. Beat until smooth.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Gradually pour egg yolk mixture over egg whites, folding gently until blended.
Do not beat or stir.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until the cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Invert pan on rack to cool completely.

title: spicy salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Mix in package of cherry jello.
Reheat, if necessary, to dissolve red hots.
Add applesauce.
Chill to set.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and put in a sheet pan and bake. Mix pineapple with sugar and bring to a boil, approximately 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over cake while still hot.
Let cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box and add sour cream.
Spread on cooled cake.
Wait about 10 minutes and spread Cool Whip on top.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Use 1/3 cup of mix for each cup of hot water.
Store in airtight container.
Great for winter parties!

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine bread pieces, milk and egg and mix well.
Add onion, catsup and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and mix with hands.
When this is mixed thoroughly, put into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Just before it's done, spread catsup on top and finish cooking.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water for 10 minutes.
Add oleo; after oleo melts, add 1 cup of cold water and sugar.
Sift flour with cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to raisin mixture.
Stir well and pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Process Oreo cookies.
(Can put in big plastic bag and crush.) Blend cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar; set aside. Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend with cream cheese mixture.
Place cookie crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (reserving some for sprinkling on top).
Add pudding mixture and remaining crumbs on top.
Must refrigerate to set.
Serve cold.

title: original chex party mix(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt; mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into large bowl.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture.
Shake or stir around. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring thoroughly every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with dressing.
Mix soups and chicken.

title: caramel cake
directions: Beat sugar, cream cheese, butter and margarine for 10 minutes. Add 1/2 cup flour and 1 egg at a time.
Start and end with flour. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Heat 1/2 cup water and syrup to boiling.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Add to syrup and cook, stirring until thick. Remove from stove and add crushed strawberries and food coloring. Cool to just lukewarm.
Coat bottom of crusts with glaze.
Slice strawberries in pie shells and spoon glaze over berries slowly so it goes down in berries.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze in trays or convenient size pan.
You can use any choice of fruits you desire.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Nuke (microwave) potatoes.
Saute onion in oil or butter.
Cut up cooked potatoes and add seasoning and cook until potatoes are browned.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place fat in heavy pan.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Add onion and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low flame for 1 hour.
Remove garlic from sauce.
This sauce may be used for basting meat or chicken while cooking or as a hot dip for meats at the table.
Contains 240 calories.
Each tablespoon has 9 calories.

title: blueberries in muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Add blueberries; stir well.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Makes 14 to 16 muffins.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scrunchies
directions: Mix together the oleo, powdered sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and chill overnight.

title: smothered steak and mushroom casserole
directions: Brown steak.
Mix other ingredients (except onion rings) together.
Pour mixture over browned meat.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer (Crust):
Mix 1 stick of melted butter and 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Form crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel the squash.
Mix squash, diced onion, salt and sugar in a pot
with water.
Boil for 15 minutes, then drain.
In a separate bowl, mix melted margarine, flour, eggs, milk and grated cheese. Add cooked squash to bowl.
Mix together, then pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add chicken cubes.
Brown on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Add onion and pepper in same skillet.
Cook, stirring it, for 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth.
Add chicken and reduce heat, simmering for 5 minutes or until the chicken is tender.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in 2-quart saucepan.
Mix well over medium heat.
Bring to boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well until dissolved.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 5 pounds. Can be refrigerated if cool.

title: italian flatbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and water until stiff dough forms.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix; gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Shape into ball; knead 60 times.
Pat dough into 11-inch square on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread margarine over dough.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: grandma b's parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add butter and 1-1/2 pts. flour.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise until light.
Add rest of flour or enough to make a dough, add salt. Knead well and let rise.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter.
Crease through with dull edge of knife and fold over.
Let rise until light and bake about 10 minutes in moderate oven.

title: 4th of july pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Let mixture cool for 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour pudding mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Place strawberries in circle on outer edge of pie.
Place one in center.
Place blueberries over remaining pudding.
Served chilled with whipped cream on top.

title: peach or apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, spices and food coloring.
Bring to boil, remove from heat, add butter and set aside.
Add all dry ingredients together and shortening and milk.
Mix well.
Roll out dough.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick 6-inch squares.
Put whole peach or apple into each square.
Sprinkle fruit with sugar and spices. Dot with butter.
Fold in corners and pinch together.
Put into buttered baking pan.
Pour syrup into buttered baking pan.
Pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, molasses and 1 teaspoon ginger with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Frost.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the oleo; add sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook prunes, remove seeds and chop.
Combine dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef and spaghetti casserole
directions: Slightly brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato paste and tomato soup into meat and stir in well.
Add 1/2 cup water and stir in.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Stir in.
Put into casserole. Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine the navy or pea beans and 6 cups water; boil for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and bake for 3 hours.
Add boiling water as needed.
When done, remove lid and let beans brown.

title: peanut oat chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first seven ingredients.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and stir.
Add rolled oats, chocolate bits and peanuts and mix.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter or Crisco together.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs, mixing well.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk.
Bake 1 hour or until cake is done in a 350° oven.

title: simply salsa
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sprite, then freeze. Remain frozen until time to serve. Let set out a few minutes to partially thaw. Add Sprite to suit your taste.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in two greased casserole dishes. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Freeze one and bake the other at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 casseroles each.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canning corn salad
directions: Cut fine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 5 ingredients and boil 20 minutes, then jar and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli in very hot water. Break into bite size pieces. Mix chopped onion into broccoli pieces. Add grated cheese, salt and pepper.

title: beans 'n' rice salad
directions: Combine rice, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and butter in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Place rice in bowl and refrigerate. When chilled, add beans, tomato, celery, green pepper and onion to rice.
In jar, combine remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, chili powder and vinegar.
Add oil; cover and shake vigorously.
Pour over rice mixture and toss gently.

title: baked chicken and broccoli(low-salt, low-cholesterol)
directions: Cook broccoli 2 minutes
less than directed on package. Drain. Spread on bottom
of
baking
dish.
Melt
margarine. Blend
in flour and pepper.
Add
broth
and
milk.
(Best
to remove from heat while
adding.)
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes. Add cheese.
Pour half the sauce over broccoli.
Add chicken; cover with
rest
of sauce.
Bake 10 minutes or more in 425° oven or until slightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water to make 1 gallon.
Place tea, cinnamon and cloves in large saucepan. Pour remaining 2 cups boiling water over this.
Heat for 20 minutes (don't boil).
Remove and strain.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Stir into jello mixture.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: butterscotch pull aparts
directions: Place rolls in greased tube pan.
Mix sugar, pudding and cinnamon and sprinkle on rolls.
Pour melted butter on sprinkle mixture.
Leave out overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and turn out on dish.
Use a large plate because this makes a large coffee cake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Coat pizza pan with Pam.
Place cookie dough on pan (starting in middle and work outwards) until
pan is covered.
Bake according to directions.
cool completely.
Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on dough.
Arrange fruit.
Mix juice with gelatin, bring to boil.
Stir occasionally.
Cool until slightly thicken.
Spread on fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put all dry ingredients into large percolator and cider into pot; let perk.

title: fastest cake in the west
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped cream or with frosting.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together; put in container and freeze.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: old timey dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl.
Pour in milk and mix briskly with a fork, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop dumplings by heaping teaspoonfuls into boiling kettle of liquid.
Cover kettle snugly.
Cook for 12 minutes exactly (no peeking).

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients; refrigerate.
Bake as needed in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Recipe will keep up to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased 9 x 9 pan for 30 minutes at 350°. For a 8 x 8 pan bake 5 minutes longer. To double this recipe bake in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Add sausage and sour cream.
Beat until mixed well. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate at least 2 to 3 hours.
Keeps well for several days.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix in order
given.
Bake
in 2 loaf pans for 45 to 60 minutes.
Start at 325° and turn back to 250° for last half of time.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and put into crock-pot.
Cook on low all day (8 hours).
Have plenty of water (to top ring of crock-pot).
You can add hot pepper if you like a hot taste.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Brown beans can be used.
Use brown or white rice.
Boil according to package directions.
Serve over rice.

title: easy onion rings
directions: Slice the onions and separate into rings.
Place in a container and cover with buttermilk.
Cover tightly and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
To cook, shake gently to remove excess buttermilk and dredge in flour.
Fry in a skillet or deep-fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, egg, sugar and buttermilk or sour milk. Sour milk can be made by adding 1 teaspoon vinegar to 1 cup milk.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost immediately with juice of 1 orange mixed with powdered sugar to spreading consistency.

title: mrs. swift's sunshine salad
directions: Use the usual method for jello, using measurements above. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: restaurant style cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: warm cider
directions: Pour cider into large saucepan.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Stick cloves into unpeeled orange.
Add the clove stuffed orange and allspice to cider.
Simmer the cider for 15 minutes.
Stir a few times with a spoon.
Let cider cool for 10 minutes.
Put strainer over punch bowl.
Pour cider slowly into bowl through the strainer.
Discard orange, allspice and cinnamon sticks.
Serve in punch cups while still warm.
Serves 8.

title: antipasto
directions: Roasted red peppers:
Roast red or green peppers on top rack in broiler.
Blacken on all sides.
Remove from broiler, place in plastic bag and seal for 10 minutes.
Remove from bag, remove blackened outside, seed and rinse.
Cut into narrow strips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers and butter).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top. Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix bean dip and cream cheese together.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch platter.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and spread on top of first mixture.
Cut onions and tomatoes and spread on top.
Finally, top with taco cheese.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients into the mixture, stir and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Cool and cut.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and flour to consistency to knead. Knead well. Roll out thin on floured paper. Sprinkle with sugar and cut with cookie cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet. Cook in 350° oven until light brown.

title: wonderful fruit salad
directions: You may add:
cut-up oranges, grapes, melon or walnuts; sprinkle coconut on top.

title: hidden valley crackers
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Store in airtight container.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugars, shortening and cinnamon like pie crust.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping.
To the remaining mixture, add the salt, baking soda, vanilla and eggs.
Stir until mixed.
Add the buttermilk and blend until smooth.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured spring-form angel food pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture lightly over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until the cake tests done.
Cool before removing from the pan.

title: rolled flank steak
directions: Pound flank steak to tenderize several hours before cooking. Score steak in diagonal cuts.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper or garlic salt and parsley.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix celery soup with rice and milk; pour into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place lightly salted and peppered chicken pieces on the rice mixture.
Sprinkle evenly with dry onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until thoroughly cooked.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Place rice and water in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Drop spoonfuls of soup 3-inches apart.
Top with broccoli, then place chicken pieces and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer to brown chicken.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: butter ball coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.

Grease 9-inch round layer pan. Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon.	Place 15 biscuits around the outer part overlapping to make a circle. Overlap remaining 5 biscuits to fill center.
Pour remaining butter over biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts.	Bake 25-30 minutes. Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6-8.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry together the hamburger, bacon, onion and pork and beans. Drain butter beans and kidney beans.
Mix all with sugar and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
You can use any type beans.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top; bake additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Combine soup, chilies, onion, sour cream and milk.
Using deep, greased casserole, layer tortillas, chicken pieces, sauce and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, covered, then for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Break graham crackers in half and place one-half on paper plate.
Top with 1/4 Hershey candy bar and 1 marshmallow.
Heat on Full power for 20 seconds.
Top with second half of graham cracker.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Cut oven off. Leave in oven to dry out.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Arrange raspberries on bottom of crust. Slowly pour cheese mixture over fruit. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Top cheesecake with chocolate glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil a pan of water with the whole chicken in it. Cook the chicken in the boiling water until done. Remove chicken from water and debone when cool. Do not discard water. This will become the broth for the dumplings.

title: caramel fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt the butter.
Add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add evaporated milk and continue stirring until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating hard until it's of fudgelike consistency (about 2 minutes).
Stir in nuts and pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Chill.
Yield:
3 dozen pieces.

title: china beach broccoli(micro magic)
directions: Trim broccoli and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Put into 1-quart micro-safe, cover and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Combine lemon juice, soy sauce, sesame seed and garlic powder (to taste) and pour mixture over broccoli, tossing to coat evenly.
May be chilled or served warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: diabetic - hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift flour, granulated sugar replacement, baking soda and salt into medium mixing bowl.
Melt 1 square of the bitter chocolate. Add vinegar, milk, shortening and the melted chocolate to flour mixture; stir to blend.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square dish; sprinkle with brown sugar replacement.
Add remaining chocolate to the boiling water; heat until chocolate is melted. Pour chocolate-water mixture over pudding batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm from baking dish.
Yields 10 servings.

title: turkey stuffed peppers
directions: To precook peppers, add pepper halves to boiling water and cook 10 minutes or until almost tender; drain and set aside.

title: posh squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash 5 to 10 minutes until tender.
Saute onion and pepper.
Place squash, onion and pepper in food processor and process until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved cheese and butter.

title: sausage bake
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Place tuna in casserole dish; add undiluted soup.
Cover with chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party grapes
directions: Wash grapes and let dry.
Mix yogurt, sugar substitute and cinnamon, then mix well with grapes.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: banana-pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in bananas, pecans, lemon peel and egg just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter evenly into loaf pan.
Bake bread 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly about 1 hour at 300°.

title: pasta pantanesca
directions: Cook garlic and mushrooms in olive oil for 2 minutes; add parsley, oregano, basil and olives, then black pepper and tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes.
Place over fresh cooked spaghetti and let sit 30 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Juice lemons. Prepare orange juice according to directions on can.
Blend bananas in blender.
Combine sugar-water mixture with lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze in 5 (1-quart) containers.
(Clean milk cartons work very well.)

title: mock prime rib
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Mix broth, Italian dressing mix and au jus mix together.
Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours. Potato and carrots may be added last 2 to 3 hours, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Mix together soup and Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Put a layer of stuffing in dish.
Add about half of chicken on top.
Then put another layer of stuffing.
Top with rest of chicken.
Put margarine in hot chicken broth and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour and sugar.
In a pot, combine the oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to a boil and pour into sugar-flour mixture. When thoroughly mixed, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Should be firm, but waxy.
Use large rectangular pan. Cool.

title: ethel's cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening and blend well. Combine eggs with 1 c. milk.
Add to the dough.
Yield 4 3/4 lbs.

title: divinity
directions: Place
first
ingredients in saucepan over low heat, stirring
until sugar is dissolved.
Let cook without stirring until
temperature reaches 255°.
Remove from heat and pour in a fine stream into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat egg whites mixture,
while
adding
sugar
mixture, until it is no longer glossy and
it holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.
May top with cherries or a whole pecan.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Sprinkle chopped tomatoes with salt and let stand while you chop onions and peppers, then squeeze and discard juice from tomatoes. Pour vinegar into a large kettle and bring to a boil; add tomatoes, onions and peppers and let cook until it changes color (somewhat brown) until done.
Add sugar.
Tie pickling spices in a cloth and add to mixture.
Let mixture cook about 30 minutes. Remove spices before filling prepared jars.

title: diet applesauce bread
directions: Crumble bread and add dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine egg, butter extract and applesauce.
Combine the two and mix until smooth.
Bake in a 2 x 4-inch loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: teriyaki beef stir-fry(light recipe)
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Cut into strips.
Combine next 5 ingredients in an 8-inch square pan.
Add steak to marinade; turn to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes to 1 hour. Coat a wok or electric skillet with cooking spray; add oil and turn to medium-high heat (325°).
Add steak, onion, pepper and broccoli; cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and tomato; cook an additional 3 minutes or until done.
Yields 4 (3 ounce) servings.

title: fancy fruit pizza
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt margarine in a round casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until light brown and set.
Serves 8.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wings at joint.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy.
Drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Heat.
Dip wings in sauce and coat completely.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn; baste with more sauce. Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Measure flour, salt and baking powder in small bowl and sift together.
Melt butter and cocoa over heat.

title: green beans
directions: Cut beans into 1/2-inch pieces and cook with olive oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper until all water has been absorbed.
Stir in vinegar and serve chilled.
Also, try waxed beans or beets this delightful summer way.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions, bell pepper and olives.
Cook until onions are done.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Cook on medium heat for 1/2 hour.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
Mix cooked rice to sauce and let stand for about 1/2 hour.

title: quick bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The batter should be lumpy.
Spoon into oiled muffin tin and bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 muffins.

title: heidi's delight
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator for 15 minutes the jello, water and ice cream.
Add pineapple, banana and mandarin oranges.
Top with chopped pecans and let set all day.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and combine with Bisquick and sausage.
Mix together with hands.
Form into bite-size balls.
Bake on baking sheet for 15 minutes at 350°, until golden.
Makes 1 tray of hors d'oeuvres.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix and pat into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put Topping over top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together; add eggs, molasses and milk; stir.
Add oatmeal, blending well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top before baking at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry salt pork in skillet until brown and crisp; remove and drain.
Saute onions in remaining fat until golden brown and clear.
Add water, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add clams with liquid; heat.
Add milk and cream, season to taste.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Do not boil!
Serve in bowls topped with salt pork.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned apple butter
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.
Do not peel.
Combine apples and apple juice in lightly oiled crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 18 hours or high for 2 to 4 hours.
When fruit is tender, put through a food mill to remove peel.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Mix ingredients into vegetables and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: green split pea soup
directions: In soup kettle, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add carrot, onion and celery.
Heat just until tender.
When veggies are tender, add split peas and 2 quarts water and a ham bone or ham and 1/2 gallon of beef or chicken broth.
Boil rapidly for a few minutes and skim off residue which comes to top.
Reduce heat and allow to simmer for 2 hours, adding water if needed.
Season to taste.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Heat on medium, stirring occasionally.
You can top with cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef burgundy with rice
directions: Brown onions and remove from pan. Add oil. Brown beef well on all sides. Sprinkle beef with flour and seasonings. Stir in bouillon and wine. Simmer slowly for two hours or until tender. Add more bouillon and wine if needed to keep meat covered with liquid.
Return onions and add mushrooms. Cook 30 minutes or longer. Serve over rice.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter slowly.
Add syrup.
Heat and add sugar.
Cook until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat, add soda.
Cover the popcorn and mix well.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: favorite swiss steak
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet and brown meat on both sides.
Combine soup, water, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Top with onion and green pepper slices.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours or until tender.
May also bake in oven.

title: dirt cake(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Crush cookies in food processor; set aside. Mix milk and pudding, then add to cream cheese mixture. Fold in whipped topping. Beginning and ending, layer crumbs and pudding mixture into flower pot; refrigerate for several hours and serve with shovel. May add gummi worms or flowers.

title: hash brown & sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add potatoes, soup, cheese whiz, sour cream, onion,
salt and pepper mix well.
Add sausage spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party eggs(makes two 9 x 13-inch pans)
directions: Night before serving:
Butter 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Lay cubed bread and cheese in bottom.
Put browned sausage or ham on top. Beat eggs and regular milk, prepared mustard, salt and pepper. Divide mixture, pouring over bread and cheese, etc.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix evaporated milk and soup.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last half hour.
Let set a bit before serving.
Good for Christmas morning or Easter breakfast!

title: sugarless cookies
directions: In large bowl, with wooden spoon, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, about 2-inches apart.
Bake about 20 minutes until lightly browned in a 375° oven.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan except cheese. When sauce is hot, add cheese and stir until blended.

title: potato candy
directions: Smash the peeled baked potato. Add powdered sugar until the mix is stiff.
Roll out on wax paper.
Spread peanut butter in a thin layer over potato and sugar mixture.
Roll up and put in refrigerator.
Chill for about an hour.
Cut into small pieces. Store in the refrigerator.
Ready to eat anytime!

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease deep dish pie pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot mousse tart
directions: In a saucepan cook the sliced carrots in salted boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Spread the margarine liberally on the sides and on the bottom of an 8-inch cake pan.
Beginning in center of bottom of pan arrange the carrot slices, slightly overlapping in circles around pan covering bottom.
Then put a row overlapping around the sides.
The margarine helps to hold the carrots on side.
Set aside.

title: sand cake
directions: Stir well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix
together.
Baste
meat (skinless chicken, steak or fish). Let
stand
for
30 minutes or longer in refrigerator. Grill on charcoal grill or pan fry on high heat to sear meat.

title: jan's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar,
add
eggs,
add 2 cups flour. Mix well.
Add	remaining
flour to fruits and nuts.
Mix well and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cover the first hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges and apples; mix. Cover with 1 1/2 cups sugar and let stand 1 hour. Do not mix sugar in until 1 hour. Mix Jell-O and 1 1/4 cups boiling water and leave to jell, but not stiff, then add to cranberry mixture.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans. Put 1 can in bottom of dish.
Place cheese on top.
Put onion rings on cheese and top with remaining beans.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Divide frosting in half mixing one half with red food coloring, other half with yellow.
Mix coconut with green food coloring. Take one Nilla wafer for bottom bun, use red frosting to attach to cookie.
Put green coconut on top of cookie.
Place yellow frosting on bottom of Nilla wafer.
This will look like cheese when pressed to the coconut and chocolate cookie.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water; add orange juice.
Chill until thick; add oranges and pecans.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish; chill until set.
Dissolve remaining gelatin in remaining boiling water.
Mix in ice cream by spoonfuls until melted; add bananas.
Chill until mixture mounds on spoon; spoon onto top of congealed layer.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12. Decorate top with Planters pecan halves.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar and oil in bowl; add eggs and beat well.
Sift soda, flour and salt together.
Add flour, buttermilk and cereal together alternately.
Put in muffin cups (greased) or with muffin papers and bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: green's salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in cottage cheese; add pineapple.
Mix in Cool Whip and keep cold until ready to use.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add instant pudding mixes to cold milk.
Mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk, and Cool Whip.
Pour over layered bananas and vanilla wafers.
Let set in refrigerator until firm (better overnight). Add remaining Cool Whip to top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Add 2/3 cup nuts (chopped).
Stir into batter.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: imitation maple syrup
directions: Place all ingredients into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
After reaching boiling point, remove from heat immediately.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Score cucumbers lengthwise by pressing through the skin. Slice thinly and place in a colander.
Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let drain for 30 minutes, then place the cucumbers between paper towels and pat dry.
Meanwhile, heat sesame seeds in a dry frying pan, shaking them frequently until they begin to jump in pan and are toasted.
Mix other ingredients into cucumbers and marinate for several hours.

title: golden catfish fillets
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
In another shallow bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Dip fillets into eggs and coat with cornmeal mixture.
Heat 1/4 of oil in a large skillet and pan fry over medium heat for 3 - 4 minutes on each side.

title: pork with apples, calvados and apple cider
directions: Place pork slices between plastic wrap.
Using mallet, pound pork slices to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cover tightly and refrigerate. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy, large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add apples and sugar to skillet and saute until golden brown, about 6 minutes.
Set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt the butter in a deep heavy pan.
Add the sliced potatoes and 3/4 or all of the leeks with 1/2 cup water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat until the vegetables are soft and mushy.
Pour in the milk and 1 cup of water.
Stir over low heat until the soup comes to a boil.
Remove from the heat and let stand 15 minutes, then puree in an electric blender.
Beat the egg yolks with the heavy cream in a separate bowl.
Stir the yolk mixture into the soup over low heat; do not boil.

title: the best baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp. Crumble. Leave small amount fat to saute onion.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Wash and then steam broccoli approximately 8 minutes.
Saute onion and bay leaf until onion is clear.
Discard bay leaf.
Heat milk and thicken with flour.
Add chicken broth and seasonings. Add broccoli and onion, then half the grated cheese.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, transfer to oven casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Heat in medium oven just until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: cajun mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: papa burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form burgers.
Grill outdoors or on the stove in a pan.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Rinse broccoli in hot water and drain well.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and bread.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead.

title: low-fat scallop or shrimp pasta
directions: Saute garlic and oil in nonstick pan for 1 minute.
Add scallops or shrimp and simmer until opaque.
Remove scallops or shrimp and set aside.
Add cornstarch and mix until thickened.
Add mushrooms, tomato, green onions and Italian herb blend and simmer 3 minutes.
Add vermouth and lemon juice and cook 2 minutes.
Mix scallops or shrimp with pepper and parsley.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
To the stock, add diced onions, potatoes, garlic, hot peppers, cayenne pepper and tomatoes.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add tomato paste, diced chicken and English peas.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken with more tomato paste or flour mixture, if necessary.
Add corn just before serving and stir frequently to keep from scorching.

title: picante potatoes
directions: Spray 9 x 11 ovenproof dish with cooking spray.
Cut unpeeled potatoes crosswise into 1/8 or 1/4 inch slices, being careful not to cut all the way through so the potato remains intact.
Place cut side up in dish.
Slip onion slices in between cuts in potato, rounded side up. Pour 1/2 cup water
into dish.

Pour butter evenly over potatoes; sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven at 425° 1 hour 15 minutes or until fork tender. Remove from oven; spoon picante sauce evenly over each potato. Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven and bake uncovered just until cheese is melted.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda and popcorn.
Bring to boil in microwave.
Cook on High for 2 minutes more.
Remove form microwave and stir in soda.
Put popped corn in grocery bag.
Pour syrup over corn.
Shake.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake. Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening well.
Combine orange juice and rind in beaten egg.
Pour all at once over dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen.
Carefully fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Spread to corners higher than center.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pigs in blanket
directions: Place cabbage in bottom of casserole.
Fry hamburg with onion, salt and pepper and put on top of cabbage.
Put on top the sliced potatoes.
Keep layering until all is used up.
Cover with soup and water (mixed together).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion and milk; form balls. Roll in cracker crumbs. Brown in Crisco. Add 3/4 cup water with the cream of mushroom soup. Cook in casserole dish in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vegie pie
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add chicken, water and curry powder.
Put into casserole.
Cover with biscuits.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and 1/2 package of cheese in a saucepan over medium heat.
After cheese has melted, add cooked rice to mixture.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Layer the bottom of a casserole dish with part of the broccoli.
Add a layer of the cheesy rice on top of the broccoli.
Continue to alternate broccoli and cheesy rice until all is used.
Place remaining cheese on top.
Cook at 425° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbling.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine butter and sugar in a large bowl, stirring well.
Add yeast mixture and egg, stirring until blended.
Gradually stir in flour. (Mixture will resemble batter rather than dough.)
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 8 hours or up to 3 days before using. Spoon dough into lightly greased muffin pans, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt in enamel dishpan.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse 2 to 3 times with clear water.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper, cornstarch, celery seed, mustard and turmeric to squash mixture.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes. Put mixture in jars and seal.
Makes 15 pints.
This is good on hot dogs and served with vegetables.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Stir all together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice while cake is hot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brown meat with onion and seasoning mix. Stir in refried beans and mix well over low heat. Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles and place in ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Press over bottom and 1/2 up sides of pan to form crust. Seal any perforations. Spoon meat mixture over dough. Top with Velveeta cheese and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Delicious topped with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream.
Add in flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add in zucchini, walnuts and raisins; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Cut peppers into strips; slice onions into rings.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add green peppers and onions.
Saute 10 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.
Add chops to oil remaining in skillet.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Remove.
Pour off remaining oil.
Pour tomatoes into skillet.
Stir to scrape up all brown bits on bottom of skillet.
Stir in salad dressing mix.
Put green peppers, onions and chops back into skillet.
Cover.
Bring to boiling; lower heat to simmer.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: becks banana bread
directions: Grease loaf pans.
Mix melted margarine with sugar.
Cream together.
Add vanilla.
Separate 2 eggs.
Add yolks to mixture. Add flour.
Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Add this to mixture.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Slightly beat egg whites; add along with nuts.
Bake in Bundt or bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield: 1 large loaf or two small loaves.

title: lemon punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water. Add juices and cold water. Chill thoroughly. Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix in baking powder and flour.
Put half of the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour can of cherry pie mix over it.
Spread remaining batter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Beat all ingredients, except cereal and topping on low speed for 2 minutes. Fold in cereal.
Spread in pan and sprinkle with topping.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot oatmeal bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and blend.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining ingredients into greased 13-inch pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs and coconut. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cut when cool.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Saute mushrooms and 1/2 cup spinach in butter.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg. Blend 1/4 cup grated cheese and 3 eggs.
Add enough cream to make about 1 1/2 to 2 cups.
Pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: mincemeat(deer meat)
directions: Cook the meat; let cool.
Grind the ingredients with the finest grinder.
Add about 1 1/2 cups meat stock or water to start boiling.
Add more, if needed.
Mix all together; simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Put in jars; put in pressure canner and process.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Set on high for exactly 1 minute. Serves 2.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add baking soda, garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Reduce heat; add milk and butter.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts or 6 servings.
Garnish each bowl with a sprig of parsley.

title: ham and dill cheesy roll-ups
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Put 2 thin ham slices together.
Spread with cream cheese.
Take a dill pickle and roll it up in ham and cheese.
Chill for a few hours or overnight. Just before serving, slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Put them on a tray to serve.

title: noodle bake
directions: Fry ground beef in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine in bowl the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, chopped green onion and green pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread 1/2 of the noodles.
Cover with all of cheese mixture and rest of noodles.
Pour melted butter over noodles and then add meat mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my mom's chess pie
directions: Cream butter, flour and sugar thoroughly.
Beat eggs and 1 tablespoon water slightly.
Add to mixture.
Add other tablespoon water and vanilla.
Mix and let stand 20-30 minutes. Stir and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pie or 12 tarts.

title: ma ma smith's pecan pies
directions: Put pies on pans to cook.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven down to 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rolled oats coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: *If you use dark Karo, use white sugar.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Combine whipped topping and condensed milk.
Stir into chilled pudding.

title: opossum recipe
directions: Catch an opossum; put it in a coop.
Feed it baked sweet potatoes and cornbread for about a week.
Next, kill it by breaking its neck.
Skin it; remove entrails, cut off tail and ears and wash it good, inside and out.
Another way to clean it is to dip it in water and roll it on oak ashes.
Keep it damp.
Rub it with lard until it gets real clean.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Measure all ingredients.
Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Boil until it forms a soft thread when poured from a spoon.
Add peanuts.
Boil until peanuts stop popping.
It will be golden brown.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and soda.
Stir and pour quickly on buttered cookie sheet.

title: chicken and fruit salad(must prepare ahead.)
directions: Combine chicken, apples, grapes, celery and pecans; toss gently with a few drops of lemon juice to keep fruit looking fresh.
Combine the remaining ingredients and stir until smooth. Pour over chicken mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: anne's apple pie
directions: Mix salt, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Slice apples into thin slices and arrange in pie shell.
Sprinkle dry ingredients mixture over apples.
Dot with butter.
Cover all with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all together in Dutch oven and bake 5 hours at 300°.
Stir occasionally.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and nuts in a bowl. Spread mixture on slices of ham and roll them up. Refrigerate for at least a couple of hours. Remove from refrigerator and slice into inch slices. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve. Excellent party food.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour batter into a hot greased skillet. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with butter.
Layer broccoli, then layer chicken.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine butter, bananas, eggs, vanilla and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add flour and soda.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3 loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: craig's barbeque sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and
simmer
for
25 to 30 minutes. Cool before using.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of milk.
Place ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (bread loaf).
Pour 1/3 of the soup mixture over the ground beef. Drain green beans; layer on top of ground beef.
Pour 1/2 of the remaining soup mixture on top of the green beans.
Place a single layer of Tater Tots on top of the green bean layer.
Pour remaining soup mixture over the Tater Tots.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven according to Tater Tot package directions, but add 10 to 15 minutes to baking time.
Serves 2 to 6 (depends on pan size).

title: juicy burgers
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet; add chicken gumbo soup.
Stir together good.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add 2 pieces of cheese.
If you like it a little cheesier, add another piece or 2. Stir all together and let cheese melt.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pasta with vegetables
directions: Cut carrot and zucchini in julienne strips.
Cook broccoli, carrots and zucchini in water for 4 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
In large skillet, heat oil and saute mushrooms, green onions, garlic and thyme until tender.
Combine vegetables, pasta and onion mixture; mix well.
Add margarine and Parmesan cheese.
Mix and top with sharp Cheddar.
Serves 6.

title: green chile-sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine onion, cheese and chicken.
Place 3 tablespoons on each tortilla.
Roll and place in 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and green chilies.
Pour sauce over tortillas and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and almond extract in large mixing bowl; blend.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Repeat layers and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar and cornstarch over low heat until thick.
Be careful not to burn or scorch.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with nutmeg sprinkles or cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: hot spiced apple juice
directions: Mix apple juice with sugar in a large pan.
Add cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil.
Cover pan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana shake
directions: Combine and blend in blender.
Leave until room temperature, then enjoy.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine
sugar,
eggs, evaporated milk and cooking oil. Mix on	medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended. Sift together
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add
flour mixture to egg mixture.
Mix a few minutes on low speed.
Add vanilla
and poppy seed.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
(Line pan with waxed paper which has
been greased and let paper extend up a few inches on all sides;	it's easy
to pull away the paper when cake is done). Bake
at
350° for
hour
to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Check doneness with wooden toothpick.

title: orange eggnog
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Chill and serve ice cold.

title: martha washington fruit cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add beaten eggs. Mix nuts, cherries, flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla. Bake in three 9-inch layers in 375° oven. Cool and ice with Coconut Icing.

title: grandma rhodes' penuche candy
directions: If you use milk, add 1 large lump of butter or oleo.*

title: dill pickles
directions: To each quart jar add dill, garlic and hot pepper.
Wash and pack cucumbers in jars.
Bring to a boil water, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour this over cucumbers and seal jars.

title: finnish pasties
directions: Melt shortening in hot water.
Cool and mix with flour and salt.
Refrigerate while making the filling.

title: corn chowder
directions: Stir milk with creamed corn. Add potatoes, corn and meat. Heat thoroughly. Take off heat. Add cheese. When it is melted, serve and top with chopped onions (optional).

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix chopped carrots and raisins together in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix the sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise (use enough mayonnaise to make salad moist, but not too moist).
Add dressing to carrot-raisin mixture.
A small can of crushed pineapple, drained, may be added.
Cool before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel
and
slice
potatoes,
chopped onion and hamburg. Bring to hard
boil
for 3 minutes.
Pour broth off.
Place in baking dish or
pan.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper and pour over potatoes
and
break up cheese over the mixture.
Bake at 400° about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in 1 cup of the cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Garnish with gumdrop flowers, if desired.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift flour.
Stir into sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add cornmeal and stir.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat with electric beater until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook bread mix according to directions.
Let cool and crumble.
Set aside.
Mix Mexicorn, green onions, tomatoes, black olive and bacon.
Mix some mayonnaise and small amount of sugar. In a glass bowl, layer corn bread, Mexicorn, tomato, onion, olive and bacon mix; then mayonnaise mixture.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar and mix with whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Longer is better.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine and press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Cook zucchini in microwave on High, covered with wax paper, for 4 minutes; stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Drain and reserve. Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic powder, onion, tomato sauce, salt, oregano and basil.
In bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and parsley.
Arrange half the zuucchini in a 9 x 9-inch oiled pan. Sprinkle with half the bread crumbs.
Spread half the cottage cheese mixture, then half the meat mixture.
Sprinkle half the Parmesan and half the Mozzarella.
Repeat layers except reserve the Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with reserved cheeses.
Bake until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Combine butter, cocoa, 1 cup water and shortening and bring to boil.
Then add flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: middle eastern chickpea salad
directions: Prepare chickpeas as directed on package.
When cooked, place in colander and rinse with cool water.
Place in medium serving bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well and chill before serving.
You may want to add more garlic.
Remember garlic is good for the heart!

title: mamoo's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil, skin and debone chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour over chicken.
Add peas and carrots to mixture.
If using boiled eggs, slice and place on top of chicken and soup.
Mix flour, buttermilk and melted butter together.
Pour batter over chicken mixture.
Add chicken broth over batter and do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Crust rises to top and is golden brown.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in casserole.
Brown beef and onion.
Stir in the rice and place mixture on cabbage.
Combine soup and water. Pour over mixture.
Put lid on and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream parlor hot fudge sauce
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a medium saucepan. Whisk in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat and let cool 2 minutes before whisking in butter and vanilla.
Keep refrigerated in covered jar up to 6 months.
Serve warm or cold.
May add nuts or flavored liqueur.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cook and stir onions in butter or margarine in 10-inch skillet until tender.
Remover from skillet; keep warm.
Heat Crisco in same skillet until melted.
Coat liver slices with flour, fry liver over medium heat until brown, 2 or 3 minutes on each side. Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onions during last minute of cooking to heat through.
Makes 5 servings, 340 calories per serving.

title: lemonade stands test of time(recipe of 1850; portable lemonade)
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, corn syrup, 2 to 3 cups water and lemon rind.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Pour through a fine mesh strainer.
Cool.
Store in a tightly covered jar in the refrigerator until needed.
Makes 1 1/4 cups lemon syrup base.

title: glazed sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with jackets on in water to cover until tender.
Cook, peel and slice lengthwise.
Layer 1/2 in shallow casserole.
