Add apples and cover with rest of potatoes.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and apples.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until apples are tender, basting occasionally.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: asparagus and mushrooms with pasta
directions: Peel asparagus and cut off tough end.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Lightly saute ham and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Boil large pot of salted water and cook asparagus until cooked through, 4 to 5 minutes or less.
Scoop out asparagus and save the water.
Add more water and cook pasta until al dente.
Drain.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter with oil in large skillet.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute, then add pasta. Toss to coat with oil.
Stir in cream and cheese.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Add asparagus, ham and mushrooms.
Cook to heat through.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark and chips in a roaster in a 250 degree oven.
Stir occasionally.
When melted, remove from oven and stir in spanish peanuts.
Drop by tsp. on wax paper.
Chill.
Sack up in plastic bags.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Remove from heat and add to cake mix.
Stir until well blended.
Spread into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Lightly pat chocolate chips and walnuts into cake mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add boiling water to raisins; cook for 5 minutes.
Cool. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add cooled raisins to creamed mixture; mix thoroughly.
Sift flour.
Measure and add salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients and chopped nuts; blend well into mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet, spaced 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and water. Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a greased 5 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch loaf pan. Give the toothpick test for doneness. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: egg drop soup
directions: About 15 minutes before serving.
In medium saucepan over high heat, heat 3 cups water to boiling.
Add bouillon cubes, ham and peas; heat to boiling again; cook 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small bowl with fork, beat eggs and salt slightly; stir into soup and cook, stirring until soup just begins to boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Makes 4 cups.

title: dr. pepper congealed salad
directions: Combine 2 cups of soda and cherries in saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour in Jell-O, stirring until dissolved. Chill in refrigerator for an hour. Add 2 more cups of soda. Stir well and refrigerate.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Pour salad dressing in large skillet.
Add onion, garlic and pepper.
Heat until it bubbles.
Add chicken tenders or breasts and cook over medium-high heat until done.
Serve over rice. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix.
Pour over vegetables and let stand several hours.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Add butter to milk and heat to boiling. Turn off heat.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add sugar, then flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat and add to the hot milk.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Spread meat in large roaster or large pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of tapioca over meat.
Add celery, carrots, onions, tomatoes and potatoes.
Combine 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pepper to taste.
Pour liquids over meat and vegetables.
Cover well.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a glass bowl, combine peanuts, syrup, sugar and salt (if desired).
Cook on High for 7 to 9 minutes until bubbling and peanuts are brown.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soda.
Stir quickly; wait until mixture is foamy.

title: amish cabbage
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Leave enough grease in skillet to coat cabbage, potatoes and carrots.
Slice cabbage and cut potatoes in bite size pieces.
Add carrots.
Sprinkle flour on top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar and 1 1/2 to 2 cups water.
Cook slowly from 30 to 40 minutes or until most of the liquid is gone.
Pour into dish.
Add sour cream and crumbled bacon; serve.

title: jackie's beer cheese dip
directions: Blend and place in hollowed out round bread.
Dip cubes of bread or crackers.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix together and roll in crushed pecan pieces.
Will make two rolls.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Pour over crust and place in oven at 325° to 350° (depending on your oven) for 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and cut into 2-inch squares.
Yellow cake mix may be substituted.

title: chestnut picks
directions: Soak water chestnuts in soy sauce.
Use enough to cover.
Soak at least 4 hours.
Remove chestnuts, one at a time and roll in brown sugar.
Wrap bacon around chestnut and place a toothpick through the chestnut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bacon is cooked.

title: creamy potato salad(low-fat)
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook in boiling water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Transfer to large bowl.
Stir in celery, onion and pickle relish.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, milk, mustard, salt and celery seed.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss lightly.
Carefully fold in chopped egg.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Serves 8.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add water, oil and vanilla.
Use fork to stir to moisten all.
Put in dry 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Ice with frosting (butter, cream and confectioners sugar).

title: seafood risotto
directions: Clean and devein shrimp, cut in half.
Cut scallops in half. In 3 tablespoons olive oil, saute crushed garlic.
Remove garlic. Add shrimp and scallops.
Saute 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.

title: sauce mexicana
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly until thickened; strain and cool.
This sauce may be kept in refrigerator for a week.
When ready to use, mix with tart mayonnaise dressing (1 part sauce to 2 parts mayonnaise).
Serve with fish, fried oysters and cold meats.
Approximate yield:
3/4 cup sauce.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells for approximately 10 minutes. Cool and drain. Cook spinach until soft. Chop with knife and fork and drain well. Mix all ingredients together; add the spinach to the mixture last! Place 2 tablespoons of mixture into each shell. Line bottom of pan with tomato sauce. Place in 13 x 9 baking pan (I like glass). Cover top of each shell with more sauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. ENJOY!!!

title: ham au gratin
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, asparagus, ham, mayonnaise, sour cream, cheese and mustard.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated sharp cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes or until top is golden and bubbly and dish is heated through.

title: five bean casserole(serves 12)
directions: Fry bacon and onions in large skillet over medium heat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.

title: south of the border baked fish
directions: Remove all traces of skin and bones from fish and cut 1/2-inch cubes.
Put in glass or ceramic bowl.
Add lime juice, onions and salt and stir well with a wooden spoon.
Put in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours, stirring from time to time, until the fish turns white.
Drain the fish, discarding the lime juice.
Mince or squeeze garlic; chop ginger and add to coconut milk.
Combine with fish, then add tomatoes, finely diced green or chili pepper and black pepper to taste.
Add chopped cilantro and pile fish on a plate or bowl lined with lettuce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
While hot, add cheese, butter, bread crumbs and onions.
Stir; add canned milk.
Stir; pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer potatoes on bottom. Brown pork chops and drain.
Place on top of potatoes and sprinkle with pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Cover with foil and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: joe frogger's cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt, ginger, cloves, nutmeg and allspice. Combine water and rum.
Combine baking soda with dark molasses. Cream shortening and sugar.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk; melt butter in baking dish, then add batter.
Pour peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Put flour, bread crumbs, seasonings and cheese in a bag and mix well.
Shake chicken pieces, a few at a time, to coat.
Dip coated chicken in egg, beaten with water.
Shake chicken in flour mixture again; set aside.
Fill an electric pan or large, heavy skillet with the oil (no more than 1/3 its depth).
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry chicken 11 minutes, skin side down.
Turn chicken and fry 10 to 15 minutes. Let stand at least 7 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches and mix with 1 cup sugar; let stand until sugar forms syrup.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 9-inch baking dish at 325° for glass dish.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla.
Pour batter into melted butter in baking dish.
Do not stir.
Ladle peaches onto batter evenly.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes (check at 45 minutes).

title: banana pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar
in
a
medium
bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs,	one
at
a
time, beating well after each. Stir in mashed banana and pumpkin.	Sift together dry ingredients and add to	egg
mixture.
Stir
in
nuts and pour into a greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients; bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, cut in squares.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: On stove top, bring ingredients to boil, except mushrooms. Add mushrooms; simmer until tender.
Great served with steaks!

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix all ingredients except the beets and margarine.
Over a low heat, cook until boiling.
Add sliced beets and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Serve immediately.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight. Roll into balls the size of walnuts, then coat with powdered
sugar. Grease cookie sheet and bake at 350° for no more than 10 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: In large casserole, layer vegetables as listed.
Top with meat, salt and pepper.
Add combined soup and pea liquid.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together except bread crumbs.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clara's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into two balls.
Top with additional chopped pecans if you like.
It can be frozen.

title: pennsylvania dutch pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in a small amount of hot oil. Season with salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat to heated platter. Spoon vegetables over pot roast.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll teaspoon of dough in a ball and press out thin with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, sour cream, soup and onion in buttered casserole dish.
Mix Ritz crackers, almonds and melted butter. Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Allow Cheddar cheese and cream cheese to reach room temperature. Combine cheese, cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine. Mix well until blended. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and mold into a ball. Roll ball into finely chopped dried beef until covered. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: salad supreme
directions: Take liquid from pineapple and enough water to dissolve jello according to package. Put the jello in the refrigerator until it thickens. Shred cheese and cut apples into bite sizes; you can leave the peel of the apples on to give color, if you like.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables. Toss lightly.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables and sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring twice during cooking period.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potatoes reganate
directions: Put in large frypan 3 to 4 spoons of oil, then put the potatoes in and cover with onion slices.
Cover with small pieces of tomato, then put in salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover the pan and cook on medium heat for 15 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender so that they can be cut with a fork.
During cooking time, gently mix with a spoon.

title: green chili
directions: Fry pork in olive oil until browned.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer together for 1/2 hour or more.
Pork tenderloin makes a fabulous chili.
You can use leftover pork as well.

title: iced tea punch
directions: Make 1 gallon of iced tea according to mix instructions; add Tropicana Twister orange raspberry frozen concentrate and 1 can water.
Then add ice.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: In a large skillet, fry the pork chops in oil. Set aside.
Put cabbage in skillet and cook until tender.
Boil the noodles; drain and mix with cabbage. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve with pork chops.

title: carolyn's double-quick dinner rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir sugar, half of flour and salt into yeast.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg and the shortening.
Beat in rest of flour.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Stir down raised dough. Spoon into cups, filling 1/2 full.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can sprinkle before baking with poppy or sesame seed.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir and add carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish, then add vanilla. Mix sugar, flour and milk; pour over margarine.
Place peaches over batter and pour syrup over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Mix salt, pepper and paprika together and roll strips in mixture.
Brown slowly in skillet. Add chicken soup, water and milk.
Simmer until chicken is tender. Serve over rice.

title: baked vegetables and kasha
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine kasha with egg and cook over low heat 2 minutes, until grains are dry and separated.
Add 2 cups water and cook covered for 15 minutes.
Pour kasha into shallow, oiled baking dish.
Mix with carrots, onions and sauteed mushrooms; add salt, pepper and margarine; mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except breads.
Scoop out center of bread to form a bowl shape out of the sides and bottom.
Fill with sour cream mixture.
Use the insides of bread to eat with dip.

title: hidden valley ranch crackers
directions: Pour crackers into large baking dish or roasting pan.
Whisk together oil, dry dressing mix and spices.
Pour over crackers, stirring well to coat all of the crackers.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes, stirring once.
Cool on newspaper or paper toweling. Keeps for weeks if airtight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish and cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix well.
Fill hamburger buns and wrap in foil.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: spotted butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, then oats, baking soda and salt.
Remove 2 cups of batter and set aside.
Stir cocoa into remaining batter.
Press chocolate batter into pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips.
Press reserved batter over chocolate mixture. Sprinkle with candies.
Press lightly into batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk, then add the next four ingredients.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers.
Cut bananas into slices and place over wafers.
Spread pudding mixture on top. Crush 10 to 15 additional wafers and sprinkle over pudding.
Chill for one hour.

title: fun jello delight
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions and allow to congeal. When at the medium congealed stage, fold in the sweetened whipped cream with a fork.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except bread) and put in hollowed out pumpernickel loaf.
Cut bread taken out to hollow out loaf into pieces and dip.
An additional loaf of pumpernickel or other flavor solid bread may be cut up to dip also or pieces can be torn off hollowed out loaf to dip.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In oblong 9 x 13-inch pan spread nuts on bottom of pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place coconut on top of nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together; add powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Line large dish with vanilla wafers, both bottom and sides. Mix pudding mix with milk.
Stir in condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread part of this mixture over wafers.
Cut 2 bananas in rounded pieces over this mixture and repeat same for second layer. May put vanilla wafers on top, if desired.

title: clam casino dip
directions: Saute butter, onion, garlic and peppers.
Add parsley, Tabasco, garlic powder and oregano.
Stir.
Add clams and lemon juice and Parmesan cheese.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and bacon.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: oriental turkey stir-fry
directions: Cut turkey strips 2 inch pieces.
Slice bok choy, chestnuts, mushrooms and onions.
Heat oil in wok, Dutch oven or heavy skillet on medium-high for 2-3 minute.
Add turkey. Stir-fry 3-5 minutes until turkey turns white and begins to brown; remove to plate.
Add vegetables to wok.
Stir-fry 4-5 minutes.
Combine Stir-Fry Sauce ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Add turkey. Heat and stir 2-3 minutes more until sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Yield:
Serves 6.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together corn syrup, sugar, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake pie 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edge.

title: shrimpies
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on English muffins.
Put in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out and cut into quarters. Refreeze in freezer bag for future use.
When ready to serve, put on cookie sheet in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until warm.
Enjoy!

title: tomato herb salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In food processor, combine all ingredients except cheese and process until finely minced.
If too thick add more olive oil. Add the cheese
when serving.
A good marinade for fish and poultry.
Great
served with pasta.
Freezes well (do not freeze if cheese has been added).

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Stir well (dough will be very sticky). Dust hands with powdered sugar and shape dough into 3/4-inch balls. Coat balls with powdered sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Remove to wire rack to cool. Yields 5 dozen.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Cream butter, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients with buttermilk to cream mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press in bottom of 8-inch pan.

title: brown berries
directions: Wash berries and place in sherbet dishes. Stir brown sugar into cream and spoon mixture on berries.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, margarine and salt.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and vinegar.
Pour over hot green beans.
(Use 1/2 recipe for 1 package frozen green beans.)

title: dijon asparagus salad
directions: In
a
large
saucepan, cook linguine in lightly salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add asparagus and cook additional 3 to 4 minutes, until linguine is tender but still slightly firm and asparagus is crisp-tender.	Drain and rinse with cold water. Drain thoroughly.
Turn into bowl and add tomatoes and onion.
In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, mustard, salt and
pepper. Add
to
pasta
mixture.
Toss
gently
to coat. Cover
and
chill for
2 hours or overnight.
Before serving, gently toss in nuts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into loaf pan.
Top with 1 teaspoon prepared mustard and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Spread over loaf and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Blend potato, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, singly, beating after each.
Add spices and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in buttered pan in moderate oven at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.
Use a 9-inch square baking pan.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Partially freeze steak; slice across the grain into thin strips and set aside.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water; stir in water.
Stir in soy sauce and sugar and set aside.

title: t.v. mix
directions: Mix and bake 2 hours in 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: easiest cake in the world
directions: Mix with spoon flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add apple pie filling.
Then add eggs, oil and chopped nuts.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper; mix and add with 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine the All-Bran, milk, egg and orange rind; let stand until most of the moisture is taken up.

title: presbyterian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until medium soft (about 30 minutes). Drain and let cool.
Peel potatoes and cut into bite size pieces. Place potatoes in large bowl and sprinkle generously with all salts and pepper.
Add the chopped dill pickles, bacon pieces, and the hard-boiled eggs.
(I grate them with the cheese grater right over the bowl.)

title: betty's cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs and add to sugar.
Stir together.
Add enough milk to make 2 pints of mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° until set (about 40 minutes).
Use bottom rack in oven. Do not overcook.
Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon over top to taste.

title: lemon pudding parfait
directions: In top of double boiler, whisk egg yolks, whole eggs, lemon juice, sugar, butter and lemon zest.
Cook over boiling water. Scrape pan bottom often.
Stir constantly for about 15 minutes until thick.
Strain curd through sieve into medium heat proof bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: hummingbird cake(shirley knapp)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add soda mix adding equal parts of wet and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: dream pie
directions: Drain pineapple. Set aside. Mix in large bowl the Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip. Stir in chopped nuts and pineapple. Mix thoroughly. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Cover and chill well. Makes an easy and not so heavy dessert.

title: pork chops and potatoes(microwave)
directions: In a 4-cup measure, heat soup and milk on High for 4 minutes; then stir.
In a 7 1/2 x 12-inch dish, layer potatoes and onion. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour hot soup mix over potatoes and onions.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High for 10 minutes, until potatoes are crisp.
Lightly sprinkle pork chops with garlic salt and place on potatoes, with bones to the outside of dish. Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Remove plastic and place under broiler to brown lightly.

title: heath topping cake
directions: Combine salad dressing, water and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients to liquid; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; while still warm, poke holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon. Fill holes with chocolate syrup.
Allow cake to cool.

title: hunt's chili con carne
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in beans and simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 cups.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add to pretzels.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast half on a sheet of wax paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with mallet or rolling pin.
Place one slice of ham and one slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper.
Roll lengthwise and secure with toothpicks.
Dip each chicken breast in egg.
Coat well with bread crumbs.
Melt butter and brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Reserve drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to reserved drippings and stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican chocolate wedding cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine brown sugar and butter.
Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes until light and fluffy.

Add melted chocolate and vanilla until well mixed. Reduce speed to low. Add all remaining ingredients except powdered sugar. Continue beating for 1 to 2 minutes. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes. Carefully remove from cookie sheet. Cool another 5 minutes. Roll into powdered sugar while still warm and again when cool.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add lemon; mix well. Set aside.

title: two-potato gratin
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Mince garlic.
Peel sweet and white potatoes.
Cut into thin slices. Put sweet potatoes in baking dish.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and the garlic.
Put white potatoes on top.
Add stock. Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter and combine with bread crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture over potatoes.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking until potatoes are soft and crumbs are golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots and margarine.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar.
Add to carrot mixture.
Add eggs and mix well. Butter or grease baking dish.
Pour in mixture and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Sprinkle rice on bottom of 9x13 baking pan.
Boil 3 cups water, mix in onion soup and mushroom soup.
Pour over the rice. Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: stewed pinto beans
directions: Inspect beans for rocks; rinse and soak in 5 cups of water and 1 1/2 tablespoons of salt overnight.
Add beans and the water they soaked in to Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
If using fresh tomatoes, add 1/2 cup of water.
Cook over low heat.
Simmer beans until tender, may be 3 to 5 hours.

title: corn surprise
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Microwave for about 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.

title: layered strawberry delight
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cream together margarine and 3 cups confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls over crumbs.
Spread carefully with spatula.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix.
Bake in large casserole dish for 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Make pastry shell; cool.
Wash and cap berries.
Set aside half of them (the best ones).
Mash the other berries.
Blend sugar and cornstarch; add to mashed berries.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes or until clear and very thick.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool.
Select a few of the remaining berries for garnish, if desired, or place all of the remaining berries into the pastry.
Spoon the cooled sugar/cornstarch mixture over the berries in the pastry shell and cover with whipped topping.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Chop stew beef into cubes; salt and pepper.
Boil meat in 3 cups water in Dutch oven 45 minutes or until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients, 3 more cups of water, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add cubed potatoes, frozen butter beans and okra.

title: white clam sauce for linguini
directions: Cook garlic, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper in oil for a few minutes.
Do not brown.
Add clams with liquid and wine.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook 1 pound linguini and drain.
Place in a serving dish; spoon sauce on top and serve immediately.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Fry hamburger meat.
Add onion and place in 9-inch pie plate. Spread grated cheese on top of meat.

title: mom's raisin cookies
directions: Combine water and raisins in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Gradually add to creamed mix.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and the cooked raisins.
Drop 2 inches apart on greased pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until golden brown.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Wash squash and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Put with onion in a saucepan of salted water.
Cook about 10 minutes or until squash is tender; drain.

title: soup hot dish
directions: Place potatoes, then beef in bits into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk together and pour over the potatoes and beef.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot tamales
directions: Put onions, garlic, water and Ro-Tel in blender.
Mix well with meat mixture and seasonings.

title: hot sausage on rye bread
directions: Brown meat together.
Drain off fat.
Add spices, sauce and cheese.
Mix well until it melts.
Put on bread.
Put under broiler.

title: swedish cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: hot german potato salad with bacon
directions: Boil potatoes briskly; do not overcook or they will fall apart when peeled.
Drain.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp in pan.
Drain.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, bell pepper, bread crumbs, catsup, eggs and seasonings together well, kneading with hands.
Shape into loaf.
Put in a large baking pan.
Pour tomatoes around loaf (if desired, peeled potato quarters may also be placed around loaf).
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add water as necessary.
Cover with foil after 30 minutes to prevent overbrowning.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute green pepper, onions, celery and rice in oil until vegetables are limp and rice is clear.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add V-8 juice and water to make 2 1/2 cups. Simmer until rice is tender.

title: green bean and ham soup
directions: Cook ham bone in water in 6-quart saucepan for 1 1/2 hours. Remove meat and cut in chunks.
Add to soup stock along with green beans, potatoes, onions, parsley, savory, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Skim off fat.
Just before serving, stir in cream.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: grandmother's christmas russian tea
directions: You will need cheesecloth or tea balls.

title: delicious spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Remove from pan and saute onion until tender.
Add to meat along with salt and pepper to taste, soup and water.
Add uncooked noodles and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt cube of butter in baking dish in oven at 375°.
When melted, add fresh or canned fruit.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over fruit.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Cook onions in small amount of hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Combine egg and milk; add to biscuit mix and stir only until mix is just moistened.
Add onions, half the cheese and parsley.
Spread dough into greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Drizzle melted butter over dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: carnival dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift soda and flour together 4 times.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Lastly, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Remove from pan as soon as you can handle.
(This works better if all ingredients are room temperature except sour cream.)

title: baked parmesan fish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter; then dip fish in melted butter and then in seasonings.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: december cider
directions: Combine ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks and discard.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: brunswick stew(old family recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for two hours.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix butter, milk and cocoa. Cook slowly over low heat. When mixture bubbles, remove from heat. Add box of confectioners sugar (sift if lumpy). Add vanilla and nuts. Can be put on hot cake (never fails).

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In large saucepan, cook beef over medium high heat until brown.
Saute onion, stirring, for 3 minutes; add to meat.
Add soup and chopped pepper.
Boil potatoes and mash.
Add butter and salt to taste.
Spread meat in large ovenproof dish; cover with butter.
Bake in oven preheated to 400° until potatoes are brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Heat on medium until mixture boils.
Transfer to a casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours to blend flavors.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, powdered milk and Karo syrup together.
Press into an 8-inch square pan.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Grind shrimp.
Cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp; heat.
Stir in sherry. Garnish with chopped parsley sprinkled over the top.
Serves 6.

title: cannot fail fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo together.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Line a 9
x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Spread candy. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Turn over on cutting board and peel off wax paper. Cut into pieces.

title: seven layer rainbow salad
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish (slightly oiled).

title: corn and rice casserole(preparation time: 10 minutes; cook time: 20 minutes.)
directions: Cook rice until done according to package. Add margarine, corn (drained) and add cream of chicken soup.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°. Spread cheese over top and return to oven to melt. Serves about 8 people.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix cake, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; pat 2/3 batter into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels and mix 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over first layer.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts and pat rest of batter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana smash
directions: Mix sugar and water and boil 5 minutes; cool completely.
Mix bananas and lemon juice in blender until smooth.
Mix all ingredients, except 7-Up.
Freeze this mix in plastic containers.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except poppy seeds) well. Just before turning in Bundt pan (floured and greased), add poppy seeds and mix gently by hand.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except apples.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured angel food Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 of the apples in, then the rest of batter, then apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.

title: turkey a la king(for mike robinson)
directions: Cook mushrooms in fat for 5 minutes.
Add flour, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend.
Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add green pepper, olives and turkey.
Heat and serve on toast, noodles or rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350°.
Blend sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add grated carrots and eggs.
Mix well.

title: shrimp con queso
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add the tomatoes, cheese, soup and milk.
Add shelled shrimp; cook about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg.
Pat in an 11 x 14-inch pan. Mix 3 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: In a food processor, combine the first 5 ingredients. Process, stopping and scraping down the container once or twice. Transfer to a medium serving bowl.

title: tomato beef casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, stirring well.
Add nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and hamburger together.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Using an 8 or 9-inch square baking dish, arrange in layers (sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese).
Makes 3 layers, topping with sauce and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mom's easy fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
When melted, add vanilla and stir.
Immediately pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: carol's frito salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order.
About 5 minutes before serving, add the dressing.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain cans of fruit.
Save juice of pineapple chunks.
Combine all fruit.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Ready to eat.

title: 7-up strawberry pie
directions: Make a glaze using 7-Up, sugar and cornstarch cooking until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Mix and pour strawberries in pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Stir in oats.
Mix in oil, egg and milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
I like to add 1/3 cup chopped, stewed raisins.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve
warm. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: banana orange frost
directions: Mash banana; stir in orange juice.
Beat in blender.
Add milk and orange sherbet.
Beat until smooth.
Serve on scoops of orange sherbet.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: bubble bread
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in a tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon on top.
Add pudding mix.
Sprinkle with pecans and butter.
Let rise 8 minutes in a warm spot.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Beat together until smooth:
eggs, cream cheese, sugar, almond extract and vanilla.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into the two crusts.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes or until set; cool. Chill.
Can be served with your favorite fruit topping.

title: glass candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to hard ball stage, 300° on candy thermometer. Take off heat. Add food coloring and flavoring. Quickly pour into a pan, well dusted with powdered sugar.
Let harden.
Turn pan upside down on waxed paper and hit bottom of pan.
Candy will fall out and break into pieces.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water and dissolve well. Add blueberries and let set in refrigerator until cool.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Let cream cheese and butter come to room temperature.
Mix flour, 1 teaspoon brown sugar, cream cheese and butter. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Remove dough from refrigerator; pinch into 1-inch balls.
Drop into 1-inch muffin tins and press on bottom and up sides of the tiny muffin tins.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into little shells.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Yields 24.
Goes well with ice cream.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and mayonnaise together; blend well. Put soda in warm water. Start adding the flour a little at a time and alternate the additions with the warm water and soda until all have been added. Mix well. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Mix mousse or pudding according to directions.	Cook brownies and cool.
Pull brownies apart and layer half in the bottom of a clear glass bowl.
Then layer pudding over that, then Cool Whip, and end with crushed Heath bars.
Repeat layers, ending with crushed Heath bars on top.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, peppers and chicken.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up and put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put remaining mixture over top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour and butter together; press in bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tomorrows salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Put Velveeta in crock-pot.
When melted, add hamburger and salsa.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: mama's chicken breast surprise
directions: Mix soups, milk and rice together well in bowl.
Place chicken in well-greased shallow baking dish.
Pour soup and rice mixture over chicken.
Bake for 2 hours at 275°.

title: marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Mix all together and keep in a tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
Use as needed to marinate boneless chicken breasts. Also great as a marinade for grilled shrimp or vegetables.

title: beer rolls
directions: Combine sugar and Bisquick.
Add enough beer to make a stiff dough.
Drop in greased muffin tins and let rise until dough is double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
This keeps for days.
Great for potluck dinners.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to a boil.
Stir in cheese; reduce to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: ritz dessert
directions: Mix
crackers, nuts and baking powder.	Set aside.
Beat egg whites
until
fluffy;
add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Fold
cracker mixture into egg white mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 to 15 minutes in 300° preheated oven until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, softened cream cheese, 10x sugar and pineapple.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: buffet spinach
directions: Cook spinach, drain and put into
x 9-inch casserole buttered.
Crumble bacon, mushrooms,
seasonings,
sour
cream and cheese on top, layered.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice each egg lengthwise, and remove egg yolks gently and place in a small bowl.
Refrigerate egg whites.
Mash egg yolks with a fork, combine egg yolks with Miracle Whip, pickle juice, catsup and mustard; mix until creamy.
Fill egg halves with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and chill for at least one hour.

title: corned beef - macaroni soup
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Then put the can of corned beef into the macaroni.
Then put the can of tomato juice into the soup and cook for about 15 minutes.

title: coconut bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in the sugar and coconut.
Add the egg, milk, vanilla and butter.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Divide the mixture between 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Fill each about 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake in a 350° oven for about 55 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Let loaves cool partially in pans.
Then turn out on cake rack.

title: golden apples
directions: Combine apples and orange juice in skillet.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Stir in honey and apricot preserves.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with pork or ham.

title: sausage nuggets
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix.
Make balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: polish golomki or stuffed cabbage
directions: *All beef may be used if preferred.

title: ground beef appetizers
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain and add cut up chunks of cheese, cooking until cheese melts.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and oregano. Simmer for a few minutes, then spread on rye bread slices.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze until hard. Remove from cookie sheet and put in plastic bag.
Keep frozen until ready to use.
To serve, remove as needed and bake frozen at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Great to make ahead.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Then add syrup and eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and salt.
When well mixed, add nuts.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Dough is for 1 or 2 pizzas; see assembly instructions. Dissolve yeast in hot tap water and add the sugar.
Add salt and oil after yeast has set.
Stir in flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Dough will be very sticky.
You may add more flour to make it manageable.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead until soft and elastic (about 5 minutes; add flour as needed).
Let dough rise about 1/2 hour (can be used immediately if you're in a real hurry).

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large pot.
Stir in marshmallows.
Stir frequently to avoid burning.
When marshmallows are completely melted, add cereal.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 24.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Sprinkle in seasonings and flour. Stir well. Gradually add Carnation milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Gradually add catsup.
Heat to serving temperature. Serve on toasted bun.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir the jello and the hot water.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 4 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add to the hot jello. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Cool in refrigerator about 1/2 hour.

title: mystery beans
directions: Drain all beans but baked beans.
Fry bacon and ground beef; drain off the fat and put meat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Now add onion, ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and all the beans.
Mix together with a spoon (large spoon) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Serve immediately.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine eggs, salt and sugar. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly. Add vanilla. Pour into a glass or Corning Ware baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center of custard comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, pumpkin pie spice and pecans; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire rack.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain well.
Add all other ingredients, except 1/2 of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and cook until bubbly.

title: asparagus-english pea casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, peas, soup and cheese.
Sprinkle mustard and Worcestershire sauce on top.
Melt oleo and mix with crackers. Add cracker crumb mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit into small pieces.
Mix fruit well.
Add milk and mix well.
Line angel food cake pan with foil, plus cover cake with foil and grease both sides with Wesson oil.
Heat oven to 400°; turn back to 350° and cook for 90 minutes or until done. Put a pan of water under cake while cooking.
Remove foil from top of cake 5 to 20 minutes before removing from oven.

title: corn chip dip (microwave)
directions: Using a 12x8x8 inch glass casserole dish or dish of approximate size that will fit into your microwave, layer the ingredients in the above order.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: potato flake sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugar, oil, salt, potato flake starter, water and flour.
This makes a stiff batter.

title: hangover soup
directions: Brown bacon in a Dutch oven or a 3-quart pot with a tight-fitting lid.
Remove bacon and brown onion in bacon drippings until transparent.
Add paprika, water, ham hocks, green pepper and tomato to pot; cook 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add sauerkraut and cook 20 minutes (do not overcook). Combine flour and sour cream.
Add to soup mixture along with sausage.
Debone ham hocks and return meat to sop.
Bring soup to a boil and serve with additional sour cream on the side, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve in a lettuce-lined bowl.
Serves 6.

title: potato griddle cakes
directions: Beat egg and a little milk, then add flour and remaining milk while beating.
Allow to stand for 2 hours.
Wash, peel and grate potatoes.
Add them to batter and blend thoroughly.
Season.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except oatmeal and chips.
Add eggs and shortening.
Then add oatmeal and chips.
Grease 9 x 13-inch and 8 x 8-inch pans and spread mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Roll pastry unusually thin and bake shell.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add salt, almond and grated lemon rind.
Stir in the condensed milk.
Strain lemon juice and add to mixture.
Right here the filling thickens and before you know it, it's almost ready to cut.
No cooking at all.
Turn filling into baked shell.

title: spanish tortilla
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Dice onion.
Place into a deep frying pan with about 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Cover and cook on medium heat until well done.
Beat eggs.
Remove potatoes from oil and drain.
Blend potatoes and eggs thoroughly, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Drain excess oil from frying pan.
Place ingredients in the frying pan and pat down smooth to approximately one-inch thick. (Resembles a cake.)
Cook until golden brown.
Place a plate upside down on the cake and with care, turn the cake onto the plate. Slide the cake back into the frying pan, uncooked side down.
Cook until well done (golden brown).
Cut as you would a pie.
Serve hot or cold.
Serve as is or with tomato ketchup.

title: sandwich loaf
directions: Note:
Have your favorite bakery cut bread the long way.

title: miniature orange tea muffins
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Cream the butter. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine soda and buttermilk, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Stir in orange rind, 1/4 cup orange juice, lemon extract and currants.
Fill greased miniature muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Dip top and sides of warm muffins in chilled sauce mixture.
Place on wire racks to drain.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar.
Add the melted oleo, milk and flavorings.
Pour in Pyrex dish.
Put the Pyrex dish in a pan that has water in it.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Before you put it in the oven, sprinkle nutmeg on top of mixture.

title: fruit-a-plenty pie
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup.
Set all aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf or 3 round fruit cans.

title: barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and add 1/2 cup onion in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; spoon into ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In bowl, mix milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift 2 tablespoons flour, 3/4 cup sugar and salt into medium bowl.
Stir in egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Fold in apples.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour, butter and cinnamon in small bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake for 10 minutes longer or until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown chops well in frying pan.
Blend soup, sour cream, water and parsley.
In 2-quart casserole, alternate potatoes and soup, adding salt and pepper as needed.
Top with chops.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until chops and potatoes are tender and browned.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Cut up berries and place in shell.
Combine pudding and Jell-O; add water and bring to a boil.
Pour over berries and refrigerate.
Takes a good 3 hours to set.
Gooooood!

title: best basic apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt; mix with pastry, fill with apple mixture, and dot with butter or margarine.
Adjust top crust; sprinkle with sugar for sparkle.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 50 minutes (slightly less for glass pie plate).

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Chop hard-cooked eggs. Mix all and chill.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, pie filling and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 10-inch greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350° or in 13 x 19-inch pan for approximately 45 minutes. Do not remove from pan until completely cooled.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Flavor is better after several days.

title: heloise's antique furniture polish
directions: Mix together and shake well before using.
Pour on soft cloth to apply and wipe completely dry with another clean cloth afterwards.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy slaw
directions: Toss together cabbage, onions and jalapeno pepper.
Mix ginger root, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and combine.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: play doh
directions: Mix all together; cook and stir until thick.
When cool enough to work with, knead well.
Keep in sealed container.

title: 7-up lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water, mixing well until dissolved.
Add cheese and marshmallows.
When slightly cool, add 7-Up, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a square pan and chill until firm.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Heat and boil for 10 minutes. Drain.
Add 4-quarts of hot water.
Add ham hock and diced ham and finely diced onion.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Add tomatoes last 1/2 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mostaccioli alfredo
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to package directions; drain. Combine whipping cream and butter in a Dutch oven; heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally (do not boil).
Add cheese and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Add mostaccioli and toss well. Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana macadamia nut muffins
directions: Adapted from J. P. Sill House, Cooperstown, New York.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Place in large roasting pan.

title: zucchini bake(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 2-quart baking dish.
Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl and mix.
Place layer of zucchini in baking dish and layer with some cheese mixture.
Repeat, ending with cheese mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle over casserole.
Dot with butter.
Tent with foil and bake 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake additional 20 minutes.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save at least 1 1/2 quarts of broth.
If not enough broth, use 1 can of chicken broth with water to make 1 1/2 quarts.
Saute onions and bell peppers.
Cook vermicelli in saved broth; don't drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, mashed.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Add drained peas, mushrooms, onions and peppers.
Add cheese, cut in chunks; stir until cheese is melted.
Add deboned chicken, cut in cubes; stir thoroughly.
Put in large casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Bring water to boil in saucepan; add salt and continue to cook until it dissolves.
Pour mixture over pumpkin seeds.
Cover and let stand for 24 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drain seeds and spread on large baking sheet.
Roast until seeds are dry, turning and stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pasta soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown the bacon, onion, garlic and celery in olive oil.
Add the sauce, salt and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the warm water, beans and pasta.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes; reduce and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serve with lots of cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white water cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour boiling water over it and mix well.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until brown.
Mixture should be thick.

title: sweet dill refrigerator pickles
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
In a large glass bowl combine cucumbers, onion and dill and pour cooked mixture over.
Cool, cover and refrigerate at least 3 days before serving.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 10 minutes; drain.
Mix other ingredients together with drained broccoli. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Top with finely crumbled Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy chili beans
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover. Simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Add cheese. Heat until cheese melts.

title: shrimp delight
directions: In a small saucepan, bring about a quart of water to a boil; drop the shrimp into boiling water; set off fire. Let set 3 minutes, then drain.

title: chile con queso
directions: Cube the cheeses and melt together over low heat.
After cheese melts, add cream, stirring constantly.
Add chopped tomato, chopped chilies, chopped green onion and garlic powder.
Stir to blend flavors, adding more cream if desired.
Heat for about 15 minutes.
Best if made a day ahead and reheated.

title: juanita franklin's j&j chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Cool.
Split layers, making 4.

title: surprise brownie rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a small bowl, combine the peanut butter and confectioners' sugar. Blend well and then roll into small balls (about 1/2 inch in diameter).
Place in freezer. In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Drop from tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart.
Press a peanut butter ball into center of each chocolate mound.
With slightly wet fingers, pull the chocolate dough over the peanut butter ball forming a peak.
Cookies will look like little teepees.
They will flatten slightly while baking.
Some might have a little raised mound in the center and others might flatten more.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately and place on rack to cool.
Makes 22 to 24 cookies

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into fourths.
Take each section and slice into very small pieces, keeping each section together.
Lay each section flat in a 10-inch square glass pan (or round pie pan) and cover with melted margarine.
Be sure each section is covered. Sprinkle with seasonings as desired.
Cover pan with plastic wrap tightly and bake for 10 minutes on High.
Let set for 2 minutes. Serve hot.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Mix egg, vinegar and ice water. You may have to add more water to form a ball.
Makes 4 to 5 crusts.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix in order given.
Batter will be thick.
Spread in greased pan, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 10 minutes.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Cover each layer of potatoes with onion, cheese, salt, pepper and pats of margarine.
Top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: low-sodium duchesse potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth and well blended. Heat over low heat until piping hot.
Contains about 195 calories per serving with 9 milligrams sodium per serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place 1 can of beans in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup over beans.
Repeat.
Salt and pepper. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread onion rings on top and bottom.

title: no-fry potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Drop by 1/4 cup on greased cookie sheet. Press with flat bottom glass to form patty. Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven. Turn. Bake an additional 10 minutes. Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: josephine's never fail fudge
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Cook milk and sugar to a boiling point (rolling boil), then cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over the mixed ingredients and blend well.
Put into a buttered pan and let cool.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: punkin bars
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Mix; spread on an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Frost.

title: pecan rounds(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix margarine, sugar and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Brown sausage; drain.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato soup and Italian seasoning.
Add meats to sauce mixture.
Layer as follows in a 13 x 9-inch pan: meat sauce, uncooked noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat.
End with heavy layer of meat sauce and cheese.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown ground beef with taco mix.
Add salsa and enchilada sauce.
In baking pan, layer crushed tortilla chips, meat mixture and cheese in that order.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream.

title: molasses pie
directions: With your fingers, work the butter, flour and sugar together until mixture is quite crumbly.
Beat the water, molasses and soda together.
Combine the liquid with the dry ingredients but do not beat.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: soft tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add water and seasoning mix. Simmer 15 minutes, until the liquid is reduced.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Spoon meat mixture into shells and arrange in upright position in baking pan.
Pour combined sauces evenly over shells.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: squash cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls into heated grease in frying pan. Fry on medium heat until golden brown on both sides.

title: salad #2
directions: It starts out in the store.
Then you buy it.
Then you take it home and cook it.
You just stir until it is ready.
Sometimes you put salt and pepper on it.

title: fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix in large bowl.
Add applesauce, eggs, salt and orange extract.
Beat 3 minutes until smooth and creamy.
Combine fruit, nuts and flour and mix well.
Stir into batter mixing well. Line two 8 x 8 x 3-inch loaf pans with triple thickness of wax papers or 1 layer of brown paper sack and pour into pans.
Line sides also.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 2 3/4 hours.
If gets dark on top before done, cover with paper whenever you want.
Cool in pans.
Wrap and store.
Delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend, add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Divide batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan. Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°, if potatoes are thawed, or longer if frozen.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Place onion, tomatoes and lettuce in a large salad bowl.
Toss in cheese.
Toss again with dressing and Tabasco sauce.
Remove 10 to 12 whole Doritos from bag and crush remaining chips into small pieces.
Add crushed chips to salad.
Reserve a few slices of avocado and add remaining slices to salad.
Brown meat; drain off grease and toss with beans, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 10 minutes, then add hot to salad and toss.
Decorate top of salad with whole Dorito chips and avocado slices.
Some large tomato slices may also be used.
Serve immediately.
Good for supper as a main dish.
Serve with hot buttered flour tortillas rolled up into tubes to be eaten like rolls.
Serves 6 as main dish or 12 as salad course.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Place meat in 2-quart covered casserole.
Do not season.
Pour onion soup mix over meat, then soup, lastly 7-Up.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours.
When done, remove from oven and let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
During this time, cook noodles or rice.
Serve over bed of either.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Set aside. Combine butter and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until both are melted. Remove from heat.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pastry pie dough
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt using wire blender or knives until mixture is like coarse meal (small peas).
Remove 1/4 cup mixture and add milk.
Then stir in remaining shortening mixture to form dough.
Place 1/2 mixture between 2 sheets of wax paper (12-inch square).
Lightly dampen table or countertop to keep paper from slipping. Roll gently until circle reaches edge of paper.
Ease off top paper.
Pick up bottom paper at corners. Dough will cling.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Peel off top paper. Add filling.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add shredded carrots and stir well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onions and carrots together until tender in a very large, nonstick pan.
Scramble eggs and add them.
Add meat, then rice, stirring.
Add parsley (dried), then add enough soy sauce to make it light brown.
Serve warm.

title: apple mallow crisp
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Toss with apples and cranberries. Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar and salt.
Cut margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler.
Stir in milk until smooth. Stir in pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered foil. Freeze until hard.

title: no bake mini cheesecakes
directions: Prepare filling mix as directed on box.
Mix crumb mix as directed.
Press onto bottoms of 12 cupcake cups.
Spoon in filling and garnish as desired with nuts, fruit or chocolate. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add shortening and beaten eggs to potatoes while still hot; add sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 (8 x 4-inch) cake.

title: creeping crust cherry cobbler
directions: Cook cherries and their juice with 3/4 cup sugar until sugar melts.
Melt butter; sift together 1 cup self-rising flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk.
Pour this batter over the melted butter but do not stir.
Pour cherries over the batter and again do not stir. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve plain or top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mama's punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Let cool.
Take 1/2 cake and crumble into punch bowl.
Mix pudding and add 1/2 to bowl.
Add 1/2 pineapple.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Add 2 bananas.
Spread 1/2 whipped topping.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Start over and repeat entire process.
Add cherries on top.
Cover.
Place in refrigerator.
Best when made a day ahead.

title: scotch haggis
directions: Place in large pot; boil until well done.
Grind into a large mass.
Add a like amount of raw oatmeal.
Mix well; stir in the Scotch whiskey.
After seasoning, stuff this entire mess into a well cleaned sheep's (or goat's) stomach; sew up opening.
Before placing in hot oven, pierce several small holes in the stuffed skin (to release steam so it won't explode and blow up the entire kitchen).
Bake for an hour or 2. Remove from oven; place on silver platter while the Scottish Pipe Band plays "On the Bonnie Banks of Loch Lomond."

title: persimmon freezer jam
directions: In a large enamel pan, combine puree and sugar.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring about 20 minutes.
Do not boil. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and peel.

title: 5 minute snack
directions: Heat oven to 500°. Toast bread; spread with prepared mustard or catsup. Mix ground beef and onions; spread evenly on each toast slice making sure edges are covered.
Season with salt and pepper. Place meat side up on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 3-5 min. or until meat is done. Cut in half and serve.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Mix flour and sugar. add 2 or 3 spoonfuls margarine, then add other ingredients with small amount of milk.
Stir and drop on greased cookie sheet or chill and roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple butter cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in muffin tins.

title: glazed apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add apples.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender and glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, allspice, soda, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix together oil, water, pumpkin eggs, sugar and nuts or raisins.
Add dry ingredients to moist ingredients.
Mix well. Put in well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best served next day.
Freezes well.

title: chili kila
directions: Fry meat until just done; drain off fat.
Add the next 5 ingredients and 1 cup of boiling water.
Simmer.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until cheese melts.
Serve over Fritos chips.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and soda and add.
Add nuts and drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°.

title: peach cake
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into cake mix until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat into a greased 13 X 9 baking pan. In another bowl, beat egg yolks; add the sour cream and mix well. Set aside 6 to 8 peach slices for garnish.
Cut remaining peaches into 1 inch pieces; stir into the sour cream mixture.
Spread over crust; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until the edges begin to brown.
Cool on a wire rack. Spread with Cool Whip; garnish with reserved peaches.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add soup, 1/2 soup can of water, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer ground beef mixture, tortillas and cheese.
Top off with cheese.
Sprinkle tortilla chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May substitute chicken for ground beef.

title: creamy chicken-noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and reserve.
In saucepan melt margarine and stir in flour and seasonings.
Slowly add reserved water.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and noodles, tossing gently to mix.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.	Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onions, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, brown sugar and noodles.
Add grapes and cashews just before serving.

title: hot zigidys
directions: Use as much hot dog relish as you need to moisten franks, onion and cheese.
Pull part of center portion of roll out and freeze to use as bread crumbs or stuffing.
Fill each roll with a tablespoon or two of frank and cheese mixture.
Roll each roll drug store wrap in aluminum foil.
Place on cookie sheet and heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
These may be made ahead and frozen.
You probably could wrap rolls in microwave wrap and cook 1 to 2 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add margarine, salt, 1 tablespoon sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Pour out on floured board and knead a few times.
Cut out and place in pan.
Butter tops and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake at 400° until nicely browned.

title: cereal snack
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and garlic powder to make syrup. Add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Pour sauce evenly over and mix well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Mix every 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together until done and drain.
Lay sliced cheese over hot potatoes and cover until cheese melts.
Cut Treet luncheon meat into small cubes and stir into potatoes and cheese.
Cover over with warm milk.
Serve with crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers for 3 hours in salt and cover with water. Rinse and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric and bring to boil.
Pour cucumbers into above mixture and simmer 5 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and pour vinegar mixture over.
Seal.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn as dry as possible.
Chop bell pepper and onion. May use green onions or other onions.
Slowly blend in mayonnaise. You may use more or less; if needed, add salt and pepper to taste.
You may also add tomatoes if desired.
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several days.

title: chili sauce meatballs
directions: Mix above and form into balls.
Brown, turning often to brown all sides.
Remove from pan and drain grease.

title: dijon pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Trim all visible fat from pork chops. Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place bread crumbs in shallow dish.
In another shallow dish, combine mustard and lemon juice; blend well.
Dip both sides of each chop in mustard mixture, then in bread crumbs to coat.
Place in a spray coated pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until pork is no longer pink, turning once halfway through baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mother's tater tots hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
Drain.
Add beans and soup.
