Mix.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: walker beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake at 375° for 1 hour (longer if desired).

title: special corn bread
directions: Combine Bisquick mix, corn meal and sugar in mixer bowl.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Mix in melted butter. Place in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until wood pick comes out dry.
Makes 12 squares.
You try this and you won't make corn bread any other way.

title: macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.

Add salt, pepper, onion salt, cheese, soup and enough milk to make mixture soupy. This can be cooked on top of stove until it bubbles up and put in crock-pot or cook in Pyrex dish in oven at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat with sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk; blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: tomato gravy and rice
directions: Fry bacon in frying pan until done but not crisp, cut into pieces.
Add onions and green peppers, saute until soft.
Add tomatoes and simmer 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix flour with enough water to make a smooth paste.
Add this to the other ingredients stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4-6.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Stir in apples, coconut and nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grate cheese.
Brown meat; drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except bacon drippings and cheese.
Put drippings in pan or skillet; heat.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of cornmeal meat mixture into pan over hot drippings.
Spread cheese over this. Add remainder of mixture over the cheese, spreading to edges.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Stir together milk and soup.
Add chicken, 1/2 cheese and macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake and additional 15 minutes.
(Double ingredients for larger casserole.)

title: cheese spread
directions: Grind Velveeta, sharp cheese, eggs and onion.
Mix well, then add mayonnaise or salad dressing to spreading consistency.
May add pimentos, if desired.
This keeps well.
Good for sandwiches and crackers.

title: sparkling jewel mold
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 1 cup of the boiling water. Add 1/2 cup of the cold water. Pour into 8-inch square baking pan. Dissolve 1 package of the lime gelatin in remaining 1 cup boiling water. Add remaining 1/2 cup of cold water. Pour into 8-inch square baking pan. Refrigerate both gelatins until firm, about 4 hours. Cut into 1/2 inch cubes. Bring 1 cup of the pineapple juice to boil in small saucepan. Add remaining package of lime gelatin and sugar; stir to dissolve. Add remaining 1/2 cup cold pineapple juice; refrigerate until slightly thickened. Stir combined whipped topping and dressing into lime gelatin; refrigerate until slightly thickened. Fold in gelatin cubes. Pour into 6 1/2 cup mold. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Unmold. Makes 12 servings.

title: potato salad(no mayonnaise or egg)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 20 minutes or until tender. Peel (if desired) and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Potatoes should be just warm enough to handle

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Mix last four ingredients.
Add to dry mixture then mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: zesty chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Cut up chicken. Mix together soup, mayo, broth and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Layer chicken, broccoli mixture, crackers and cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chilli burgers
directions: Add all ingredients in a saucepan; cook on high for about 15 minutes.
After ingredients are mixed, cut temperature down to simmer and cook approximately 1 hour.
Put meat on hamburger buns.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat.
Add milk and beat.
Pour into pie shell.
Chip 1/2 stick butter over top and sprinkle nutmeg. Bake at 350° until firm or about 1 hour.

title: christmas macaroni
directions: My children call it this because of red pimentos.

title: pizza pie
directions: Boil egg noodles and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain. Pour Pizza Quick sauce into ground beef and mix well.
Butter well a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour noodles into pan; dilute soup with 1/4 cup water and heat; pour over noodles.
Then pour meat and sauce over this.
Top with cheese; add pepperoni slices over top. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish with margarine. Arrange sliced potatoes in dish.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, salt and cinnamon in heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar and 1/3 cup water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and apricots.
Pour over potatoes, sprinkle with pecans. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in deep dish.
Mix dry ingredients. Add milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Add sweetened fruit and bake in moderate oven (375°).

title: low calorie casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Salt and pepper.
Stir in rice.
In a greased baking dish, layer cabbage and salt.
Spread beef over vegetables.
Mix soup with water; pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large bowl, combine ingredients. Stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour into pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: classic german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate in water; stir.
In large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to batter alternately with buttermilk until blended.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into batter.
Spread evenly into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Frost and top with Coconut Pecan Topping.

title: beef noodle soup(big batch)
directions: Boil beef soup bones for 1 1/2 hours.
Skim the scum off top as it boils.
When it looks like it's done, getting scummy on top, add salt, bay leaf and whole allspice.
Continue boiling until meat is tender.
Remove bones from water, let cool enough to touch and remove meat from bones.
Using same water, put meat back in and add tomato sauce and ketchup.
Add noodles and cook until noodles are done.
When just about done, sprinkle about 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon on top; stir and serve.
You will be adding some water to this as it's boiling.
Cooking time about 3 to 4 hours.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in water; mash all.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until real warm.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop spoonfuls of cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: merry berry holiday punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine orange juice, cranberry juice and strawberries.
Add ginger ale and ice just before serving.
Float orange slices, strawberries and mint on top.
Serves 18.

title: taco supper(makes 8 servings)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and heat for 15 minutes and serve over Fritos.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place Cheddar cheese in mixing bowl with paddle attachment. Cream until smooth.
Add processed and cream cheese.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Again, whip until fluffy.
Place mixture in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator. Remove wrap and shape mixture into a ball or other desired shape. Coat with pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: sugar-free chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 8 or 9-inch pie plate. Prepare pudding as directed.
Pour into crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients, except oils.
With motor running, add oils until creamy.
Chill and serve.

title: brown sugar apple pie
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Stir to mix.
Add apples and toss to coat.
Dump apples in pie shell and shake gently to settle.
In the same bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, flour and salt.
Use a pastry cutter or 2 knives and cut mixture until resembles coarse corn meal.
Heap on top of apples in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hearty hamburger dish
directions: Heat fat in heavy skillet; add beef and cook until browned. Add onion; cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Spoon off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mama's applesauce cake
directions: Mix apples, peaches, eggs, shortening and sugar together well. Mix dry ingredients together and add one cup at a time to batter. (Hint:
Mix a little flour over raisins and nuts before adding to batter.)
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Writers note:
Mama's original recipe had no measurement for the spices, raisins or nuts, as some who cook often and a lot use sight for measurement.
I guessed about a teaspoon of each spice and a cup each of the raisins and nuts.)

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Completely soften beans by cooking in boiling water on stove. Drain the water off the beans.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot in the order listed and stir.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: apple-raisin cake
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat the first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes (batter will be stiff).
With a spoon, stir in apples, raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer if using a Bundt pan.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking dish, blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes, turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: plucket
directions: Scald milk, oil, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine and add enough flour for bread dough.
Knead, rise 1 hour.
Punch down, roll into balls (about 2 inches).
Roll in melted butter then into mixture of cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts.
Place balls in angel pan until 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: potato salad for fifty
directions: Wash, peel, cube and boil 12 pounds Irish potatoes.
When potatoes are tender, drain and place in large container for mixing.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix together; then add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste; brown chops in shortening.
Place chops in baking dish.
Pour around the chops a mixture of 1 cup soup, 1 cup milk and 1/3 cup water.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes until chops are tender.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar and honey.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add baking soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn in baking pan.
Stir to combine and add peanuts.
Bake at 225° for about 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: vegetarian stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Scoop out inside and mash.
Mix remainder of ingredients with eggplant.
Put back in eggplant shell.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix pudding as directions on box.
Mix 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip in pudding; set aside.
Line regular cake pan (13 x 9) with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix on crackers and spread.
Line another layer of crackers and pour remaining pudding.
Line another layer of crackers.
Spread blueberry pie filling on top. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add shortening, eggs, orange rind and juice; blend well.
Stir in rolled oats.
Drop tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until done.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: zucchini with chicken soup
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Combine zucchini and onion with sour cream, cream of chicken soup, shredded carrots and 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs tossed with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine cinnamon and brown sugar. Sprinkle apples with 1/2 of the cinnamon mixture. Combine sugar, flour, egg, salt and baking powder. Spread this mixture over apples. This will act as a pie dough crust. Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mixture over dough.
Pour melted oleo over the top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat until thickened.
Pour over browned chicken, spareribs or meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or heat on top of stove with meatballs.
Watch it closely as it burns easily.

title: calico salad
directions: Use canned vegetables that have been well drained, or use frozen vegetables that have been cooked and well drained.

title: crunchy corn casserole
directions: Saute green pepper slowly in butter until soft.
Add corn, pimento, egg and 1/2 can crushed onion rings.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 25 minutes at 350° or until firm. Sprinkle other half onion rings on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: pork chops with capers
directions: Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Heat oil in nonstick frying pan. When oil is very hot, put chops in and brown them well on each side, about 5 minutes a side.
Lower heat; let chops cook about 20 more minutes.
Turn chops frequently as they cook.
Remove chops to warm platter and cover.
Discard all fat in pan.
Add capers to pan and saute briefly.
Add onion and saute.
Stir onion and capers together and brown.
Add garlic and saute.
Add vinegar and stir to remove meat particles from pan.
Add stock, tomato and any liquid around chops.
Allow sauce to fully boil.
Stir in mustard and pour mixture over sauce.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil raisins, dates, pineapple and water for 3 minutes.
Add margarine and cool.
Mix flour, soda, eggs and vanilla; add to cooled fruit mixture.
Add nuts; mix well.
Put in a 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked chop suey or hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Add the remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a covered casserole.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles; bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: fresh pear pie
directions: In a saucepan, place pears and sugar with cinnamon, orange juice and oleo and cook until pears are tender.
Then add the sugar mixed with cornstarch and cook until slightly thick.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Place pie crust strips across pie and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Add water to rice in 3-quart pan. Add onion and start cooking. Place thighs on top and cook on medium heat until water has cooked down to the rice.
(If rice is still hard, more water can be added.)
Complete cooking on low heat until chicken is tender and rice is soft.
The rice will not be dry, about 45 minutes.

title: dirt
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and sugar until creamy.
Add Cool Whip, pudding (dry) and milk.
In separate bowl, put layer of cookie crumbs, then mixture.
Keep alternating layers, ending with cookie crumbs.
Serve in bucket with shovel or flowerpot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, peanut butter and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.

title: pecan, rice and crawfish dressing
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a pot and cook over medium high heat for 10 minutes, stirring until beef crumbles and in no longer pink. Stir in crawfish and next 6 ingredients. Cook for 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: super-duper chocolate drop cookies
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Using an electric mixer at medium speed, mix the butter and the sugar in a large bowl until creamy. Add in the egg and the vanilla, beating the mixture until it is fluffy.
Blend in the melted chocolate.
Place heaping tablespoonfuls of the mixture onto greased baking sheets, leaving about 2-inches between each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes until they are firm to the touch.
Remove and let cool.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from lemon; set aside.
In skillet, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove; spoon off fat.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts and cherries.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Use powdered sugar to dip hands into as you roll balls.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Melt chocolate and paraffin on low heat and dip one piece at a time. Makes 80 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, peanuts, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon soda. Stir and pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: grandmother's pepper relish
directions: Chop onions and peppers in large pan. Cover with boiling water. Let stand 10 minutes then drain. Cover again with boiling water; let stand 10 minutes, then drain well. Mix together vinegar, sugar and salt. Pour over pepper mixture; cook for 15 minutes. Pack in jars while hot and seal. Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Press with cookie press or fancy glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar generously on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup water.
In saucepan, combine sugar, shortening and 1 cup water.
Boil until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to yeast mixture.
Combine together until flour is absorbed.
Flour a spot on your counter. Knead dough.
Cut in half and pat into 2 pizza pans or cookie sheets.
Use favorite sauce, cheeses and toppings.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Slightly brown pork chops.
Place single layer of chops in baking pan.
Cover with undiluted mushroom soup.
Cover and bake in hot oven for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable tray and dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayo together; add package Ranch dressing and blend well.
Refrigerate to season.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Cool the mixture in the refrigerator to make it easier to handle.
Roll into walnut-sized balls and coat with sugar.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheets for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine ham, eggs, celery, pickles and pimento.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Mix lightly with forks.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: betty's chicken tortillas
directions: In blender mix tomatoes and green chilies until smooth.
Add sour cream and blend; set aside.
Mix cooked chicken, cream cheese and onion together.
It will be a thick dough.
Put chicken mixture in tortillas and roll up.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and place Jack cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and chop apples into a large roaster.
Mix other ingredients in and bake at 350° for about 4 hours.
Stir once in a while.
One-half hour before done, add 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
You can freeze or can it.

title: lemon whipper snaps
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine cake mix, topping and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Mix cream cheese, chicken and green chiles together.
After mixture is well mixed, spread onto tortillas, then roll tortilla with mixture inside, then cut tortillas into bite-size pieces.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix well flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour in bottom of pan.
Add peaches and butter.
Let bake at 325°.

title: spicy creole sauce
directions: Cut shrimp or crabmeat into pieces.
Saute in olive oil, butter and garlic.
Add cayenne pepper, paprika and flour until a paste consistency.
Stir in clam juice until mixture makes a semi-thick gravy.
Serve over fish, chicken or rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add sour cream by layer in casserole.
Spread mixture with crumbs that have been mixed with the margarine.
Add rest of squash; spread with crumbs dotted with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oat baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove skin and fat from chicken pieces. Heat margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 19 x 2 inches, in oven until melted.
Mix remaining ingredients except egg whites.
Dip chicken into egg whites; coat with oat mixture.
Place meaty sides down in pan.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes turn and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until juices run clear.
6 servings.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove skin and debone. Boil spaghetti in the same pot and water the chicken was cooked in. In deep skillet melt butter and saut onions, bell pepper and mushrooms. Add soup and chicken broth. Stir in cheese until melted. Add chicken; cook until everything is well blended. Mix in noodles, pour in 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: tangy carrot coins
directions: Place carrots in saucepan, add 1 inch of water, boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 7-9 minutes.
Drain, add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat 1-2 minutes or until thickened.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and milk 45 minutes on low heat.
Add sugar; cook 10 minutes more.
Add to rice the remaining ingredients, stirring while adding.
Stir frequently.
Cook 30 minutes longer or until rice is done.

title: beef-barley soup(ingredients for 8 servings)
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add beef, cook, stirring often, until browned.
Add 8 cups water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender. With slotted spoon, remove meat to bowl.
With two forks, shred meat; set aside.
In cup, dissolve bouillon in the 1/2 c. water. Add to saucepot with tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, barley, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: blueberry slumps
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, mix blueberries and their juice with sugar.
Cook until juice starts to boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder, orange rind, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in milk until just moistened. Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls on top of simmering berries. Cover skillet and cook 15 minutes or until dough is puffed.
Serve dumplings with blueberry sauce in skillet.
Makes 8 servings.

title: angela manning's icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Pack into 2 tube pans or small bowls to give as gifts.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening. Add eggs and molasses and mix. Dissolve baking soda in boiling water. Mix. Add flour, cinnamon, cloves and raisins. Mix well. Bake at 350° for approximately 7 minutes. Frost while warm.

title: sugarless apple bran muffins
directions: Mix in a large bowl the first 7 ingredients.
Beat together the remaining ingredients. Combine and let batter stand 5 minutes. Fill muffin tins to top. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir until well blended.
Grease 2 (9-inch) plates.
Divide mixture evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potatoes in the oven
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into cake pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cook for 1 hour at 375° or until brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light.
Sift dry ingredients, except baking soda, together.
Add baking soda to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in preserves, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Can be made several weeks ahead of time and frozen until ready to eat or give.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. (May have to use your hands.) Roll into balls. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Cut bread in 1/4 to 1/2 inch pieces.
Place bread on cookie sheet; top with cheese.
Place in freezer, then place frozen in plastic bags.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes. Mix well. Fold potatoes into cheese mixture.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: steamy crab teaser
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in small casserole and top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: chunky oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet.
Beat well all ingredients.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto prepared cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake.
Store tightly covered.

title: liberty street's honey mustard dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then for 30 minutes at 375°.
Beat egg whites with the powdered sugar.
Put on pie; bake until brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.
At medium speed, blend the margarine, shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend well after each.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture with spoon.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased sheet in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread(mother's)
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add molasses and beat.
Add egg and beat.
Add hot water last.

title: mom's orange cake
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-o in 3/4 cup
boiling water and allow to cool.
Mix 1 yellow cake mix, eggs, oil and cooled Jell-O mixture and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in bundt pan for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°. Take out of pan and while still warm brush with 1/2 cup white sugar mixed with enough orange juice to dissolve sugar.

title: carrot-potato puree
directions: In saucepan, cook potato in boiling water until tender, about 7 minutes.
Drain.
In separate saucepan, boil carrots in just enough water to cover until tender, about 6 minutes.

title: azteca lasagna mexicana
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.
Line bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish with half of the tortillas, overlapping edges.
Top with half the meat mixture.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange remaining tortillas over cheese mixture.
Spread remaining meat mixture over all and top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.

title: taco salad i
directions: Prepare ground beef and taco seasoning mix as instructed on package.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: barbecued chicken or pork
directions: Using approximately 1 pound of pork ribs per person, split into sections.
Precook ribs in boiling water for 3/4 hour.
Drain thoroughly and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon sauce enough to cover and bake in a 350° oven.
Add remaining sauce halfway through cooking time.

title: caramel cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix kraut, onion, sour cream and garlic powder.
Spoon lightly into a greased 8-inch pan.
Arrange corned beef slices over the top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Remove crusts from 9 slices of rye bread.
Halve the bread into triangles and arrange over cheese, covering the top completely.
Brush with 2 tablespoons of melted butter or light margarine.
Cover and chill for 8 hours. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place 1 cup of sugar in an iron skillet and brown slowly.
To 1 1/4 cups of sugar, add 1/2 cup of flour and mix well.
Beat the 5 egg yolks together and add 2 cups of milk; add this to the sugar-flour mix gradually.
Add a pinch of salt, 2 tablespoons of butter and a teaspoon of vanilla.
Heat this mixture in a double boiler until it reaches the boiling point.
Add this mixture to the melted sugar and stir constantly until thickened.
Pour it into a pastry shell and place meringue on top.
Brown in a slow oven.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large one.

title: barbecued pork ribs
directions: Combine catsup, 1 1/2 cups water, chili sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, paprika, 2 1/4 teaspoon salt, garlic and hot pepper sauce in a large saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes, until sauce is good basting consistency.

title: quick black forest cake
directions: Mix all together well with spoon.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and glaze.
Serve as is or with whipped topping and cherry.
Serves 15.

title: homemade stuffing
directions: Mix all together.
Add enough water to moisten enough to stick together.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soups and 1 can of water.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Simmer over low heat for at least 1/2 hour.
Add additional water, if needed.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all the filling ingredients together thoroughly.
Divide the filling and spread evenly over the tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap; cut in slices 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.
Lay pinwheels flat on glass serving plate.
Garnish with parsley.
Leave space in center of plate for small bowl of salsa, if desired.
Yields about 50 pinwheels.

title: lessarella cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients on high for 1 to 2 minutes.
Cook on low,
stirring
constantly.
When thick, place in mold and chill overnight.
Remove and slice.
Use half of arrowroot for pizza or fondue.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: kentucky chicken
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter and then coat well with dry mixture.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour or more.
Baste frequently.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the flank steak.
Pour over the flank steak in a freezer bag and freeze with the flank steak in the marinade.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix the white sugar, flour, salt and egg together; set aside.
Put sliced apples, brown sugar and cinnamon (mixed together) in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put flour mixture on top of apples, then pour melted butter over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until apples are cooked.

title: my favorite easy cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box with cream cheese added to mix.

title: good salad
directions: Combine chicken, ham, celery, almonds and mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Cut egg lengthwise into eighths.
Garnish salad with egg wedges and pimientos.
Serve with hot biscuits. Makes 6 servings.

title: refrigerator cheesecake
directions: Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup cold water in a saucepan.
Warm over low heat until dissolved.
Combine dissolved gelatin with next 5 ingredients.
Whirl in blender until liquified and very smooth.
Add lemon juice.
(I add flavored jello instead of unflavored and cut back on the sugar.
Cherry pie filing is a good topping.)
Place in 9-inch graham cracker pie crust.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix well and press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered casserole (a flat 9 x 13-inch baking pan works best).
Top with butter.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: dill beef and cabbage microwave
directions: Mix all together in a greased dish.
Add seasoned bread crumbs, 1/2 cup of cheese and onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on Medium-high for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: great-grandma's economical cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into floured and greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched gently.

title: miss rose's diet pie
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving approximately 4 ounces of the Cool Whip. Put in the Crust. Top with remaining Cool Whip either spreading out or dollop with spoon.

title: ham mustard glaze recipe
directions: Add mixture to saucepan and cook slowly until thick.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Line pan with vanilla wafers.
Add the Eagle Brand and lemon juice; mix together until thick.
Add the Cool Whip.
Mix together and pour on top of cookie crust.
Add crushed vanilla wafers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: salsa
directions: Finely chop onions and hot pepper and put in small mixing bowl.
Then add tomatoes and crush all ingredients together.
Add water, salt and garlic salt and stir.

title: tomato soup
directions: Combine tomato puree, sugar, celery and onions; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Melt fat; add flour, salt and paprika.
Stir tomato mixture into milk; reheat if necessary. Serve immediately.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with Wesson oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Prick cake with fork and pour over Buttermilk Icing while hot, allowing to soak in, making a glaze.

title: oven mashed potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and cook potatoes.
Be careful not to overcook. Rice potatoes while hot.
Add butter, whipped cream and salt.
Whip all together in an electric mixer.
Divide dough into 2 cups per package.
Let cool overnight.
In the morning, add 2/3 cup flour to each bag of dough.
Mix well.
Make into a roll.
When ready to bake, cut off a portion of dough and roll out as thin as possible. Bake at 375° on a Lefse iron until brown specks appear.
Cool on racks covered with dish towels.
Cool and pack in Baggies.
Makes 25 large ones.

title: raspberry cheese dreams
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Put 1 teaspoon of crumb mixture firmly in bottom of cup.
Place in freezer.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Break up corned beef, mix with noodles, soups, milk, onion and about 1/3 of the grated cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush potato chips and sprinkle over the top, along with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
